142static bool dispatchBeforeInputEvent(Element& element, const AtomString& inputType, const String& data = { }, RefPtr<DataTransfer>&& dataTransfer = nullptr, const Vector<RefPtr<StaticRange>>& targetRanges = { }, Event::IsCancelable cancelable = Event::IsCancelable::Yes)
143{
144 if (!element.document().settings().inputEventsEnabled())
145 return true;
146
147 auto event = InputEvent::create(eventNames().beforeinputEvent, inputType, cancelable, element.document().windowProxy(), data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges, 0);
148 element.dispatchEvent(event);
149 return !event->defaultPrevented();
150}
151
152static void dispatchInputEvent(Element& element, const AtomString& inputType, const String& data = { }, RefPtr<DataTransfer>&& dataTransfer = nullptr, const Vector<RefPtr<StaticRange>>& targetRanges = { })
153{
154 if (element.document().settings().inputEventsEnabled()) {
155 // FIXME: We should not be dispatching to the scoped queue here. Normally, input events are dispatched in CompositeEditCommand::apply after the end of the scope,
156 // but TypingCommands are special in that existing TypingCommands that are applied again fire input events *from within* the scope by calling typingAddedToOpenCommand.
157 // Instead, TypingCommands should always dispatch events synchronously after the end of the scoped queue in CompositeEditCommand::apply. To work around this for the
158 // time being, just revert back to calling dispatchScopedEvent.
159 element.dispatchScopedEvent(InputEvent::create(eventNames().inputEvent, inputType, Event::IsCancelable::No,
160 element.document().windowProxy(), data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges, 0));
161 } else
162 element.dispatchInputEvent();
163}

165static String inputEventDataForEditingStyleAndAction(const StyleProperties* style, EditAction action)
166{
167 if (!style)
168 return { };
169
170 switch (action) {
171 case EditAction::SetColor:
172 return style->getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyColor);
173 case EditAction::SetInlineWritingDirection:
174 case EditAction::SetBlockWritingDirection:
175 return style->getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyDirection);
176 default:
177 return { };
178 }
179}

181static String inputEventDataForEditingStyleAndAction(EditingStyle& style, EditAction action)
182{
183 return inputEventDataForEditingStyleAndAction(style.style(), action);
184}

200EditAction ClearTextCommand::editingAction() const
201{
202 return EditAction::Delete;

204
205void ClearTextCommand::CreateAndApply(Document& document)
206{
207 if (document.selection().isNone())
208 return;
209
210 // Don't leave around stale composition state.
211 document.editor().clear();
212
213 const VisibleSelection oldSelection = document.selection().selection();
214 document.selection().selectAll();
215 auto clearCommand = adoptRef(*new ClearTextCommand(document));
216 clearCommand->setStartingSelection(oldSelection);
217 clearCommand->apply();
218}

223TemporarySelectionChange::TemporarySelectionChange(Document& document, std::optional<VisibleSelection> temporarySelection, OptionSet<TemporarySelectionOption> options)
224 : m_document(RefPtr(&document))
225 , m_options(options)
226 , m_wasIgnoringSelectionChanges(document.editor().ignoreSelectionChanges())
227#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
228 , m_appearanceUpdatesWereEnabled(document.selection().isUpdateAppearanceEnabled())
229#endif
230{
231#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
232 if (options & TemporarySelectionOption::EnableAppearanceUpdates)
233 document.selection().setUpdateAppearanceEnabled(true);
234#endif
235
236 if (options & TemporarySelectionOption::IgnoreSelectionChanges)
237 document.editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(true);
238
239 if (temporarySelection) {
240 m_selectionToRestore = document.selection().selection();
241 setSelection(temporarySelection.value());
242 }
243}
244
245TemporarySelectionChange::~TemporarySelectionChange()
246{
247 if (m_selectionToRestore)
248 setSelection(m_selectionToRestore.value());
249
250 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::IgnoreSelectionChanges) {
251 auto revealSelection = m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::RevealSelection ? Editor::RevealSelection::Yes : Editor::RevealSelection::No;
252 m_document->editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(m_wasIgnoringSelectionChanges, revealSelection);
253 }
254
255#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
256 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::EnableAppearanceUpdates)
257 m_document->selection().setUpdateAppearanceEnabled(m_appearanceUpdatesWereEnabled);
258#endif
259}
260
261void TemporarySelectionChange::setSelection(const VisibleSelection& selection)
262{
263 auto options = FrameSelection::defaultSetSelectionOptions();
264 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::DoNotSetFocus)
265 options.add(FrameSelection::DoNotSetFocus);
266 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::RevealSelection)
267 options.add(FrameSelection::RevealSelection);
268 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::SmoothScroll)
269 options.add(FrameSelection::SmoothScroll);
270 if (m_options & TemporarySelectionOption::OverrideSmoothScrollFeatureEnablment)
271 options.add(FrameSelection::OverrideSmoothScrollFeatureEnablement);
272 m_document->selection().setSelection(selection, options);
273}

275// When an event handler has moved the selection outside of a text control
276// we should use the target control's selection for this editing operation.
277VisibleSelection Editor::selectionForCommand(Event* event)
278{
279 auto selection = m_document.selection().selection();
280 if (!event)
281 return selection;
282 // If the target is a text control, and the current selection is outside of its shadow tree,
283 // then use the saved selection for that text control.
284 if (auto target = makeRefPtr(event->target()); is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(target) && downcast<Element>(*target).isTextField()) {
285 auto start = selection.start();
286 if (start.isNull() || target != enclosingTextFormControl(start)) {
287 if (auto range = downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*target).selection())
288 return { *range, Affinity::Downstream, selection.isDirectional() };
289 }
290 }
291 return selection;
292}

332bool Editor::handleTextEvent(TextEvent& event)
333{
334 LOG(Editing, "Editor %p handleTextEvent (data %s)", this, event.data().utf8().data());
335
336 // Default event handling for Drag and Drop will be handled by DragController
337 // so we leave the event for it.
338 if (event.isDrop())
339 return false;
340
341 if (event.isPaste()) {
342 if (event.pastingFragment()) {
343#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
344 if (client()->performsTwoStepPaste(event.pastingFragment()))
345 return true;
346#endif
347 replaceSelectionWithFragment(*event.pastingFragment(), SelectReplacement::No, event.shouldSmartReplace() ? SmartReplace::Yes : SmartReplace::No, event.shouldMatchStyle() ? MatchStyle::Yes : MatchStyle::No, EditAction::Paste, event.mailBlockquoteHandling());
348 } else
349 replaceSelectionWithText(event.data(), SelectReplacement::No, event.shouldSmartReplace() ? SmartReplace::Yes : SmartReplace::No, EditAction::Paste);
350 return true;
351 }
352
353 String data = event.data();
354 if (data == "\n") {
355 if (event.isLineBreak())
356 return insertLineBreak();
357 return insertParagraphSeparator();
358 }
359
360 return insertTextWithoutSendingTextEvent(data, false, &event);
361}

373enum class ClipboardEventKind {
374 Copy,
375 Cut,
376 Paste,
377 PasteAsPlainText,
378 PasteAsQuotation,
379 BeforeCopy,
380 BeforeCut,
381 BeforePaste,
382};
383
384static AtomString eventNameForClipboardEvent(ClipboardEventKind kind)
385{
386 switch (kind) {
387 case ClipboardEventKind::Copy:
388 return eventNames().copyEvent;
389 case ClipboardEventKind::Cut:
390 return eventNames().cutEvent;
391 case ClipboardEventKind::Paste:
392 case ClipboardEventKind::PasteAsPlainText:
393 case ClipboardEventKind::PasteAsQuotation:
394 return eventNames().pasteEvent;
395 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforeCopy:
396 return eventNames().beforecopyEvent;
397 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforeCut:
398 return eventNames().beforecutEvent;
399 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforePaste:
400 return eventNames().beforepasteEvent;
401 }
402 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
403 return { };
404}
405
406static Ref<DataTransfer> createDataTransferForClipboardEvent(Document& document, ClipboardEventKind kind)
407{
408 switch (kind) {
409 case ClipboardEventKind::Copy:
410 case ClipboardEventKind::Cut:
411 return DataTransfer::createForCopyAndPaste(document, DataTransfer::StoreMode::ReadWrite, makeUnique<StaticPasteboard>());
412 case ClipboardEventKind::PasteAsPlainText:
413 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().customPasteboardDataEnabled()) {
414 auto plainTextType = "text/plain"_s;
415 auto plainText = Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(document.pageID()))->readString(plainTextType);
416 auto pasteboard = makeUnique<StaticPasteboard>();
417 pasteboard->writeString(plainTextType, plainText);
418 return DataTransfer::createForCopyAndPaste(document, DataTransfer::StoreMode::Readonly, WTFMove(pasteboard));
419 }
420 FALLTHROUGH;
421 case ClipboardEventKind::Paste:
422 case ClipboardEventKind::PasteAsQuotation:
423 return DataTransfer::createForCopyAndPaste(document, DataTransfer::StoreMode::Readonly, Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(document.pageID())));
424 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforeCopy:
425 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforeCut:
426 case ClipboardEventKind::BeforePaste:
427 return DataTransfer::createForCopyAndPaste(document, DataTransfer::StoreMode::Invalid, makeUnique<StaticPasteboard>());
428 }
429 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
430 return DataTransfer::createForCopyAndPaste(document, DataTransfer::StoreMode::Invalid, makeUnique<StaticPasteboard>());
431}
432
433// Returns whether caller should continue with "the default processing", which is the same as
434// the event handler NOT setting the return value to false
435// https://w3c.github.io/clipboard-apis/#fire-a-clipboard-event
436static bool dispatchClipboardEvent(RefPtr<Element>&& target, ClipboardEventKind kind)
437{
438 // FIXME: Move the target selection code here.
439 if (!target)
440 return true;
441
442 auto dataTransfer = createDataTransferForClipboardEvent(target->document(), kind);
443
444 auto event = ClipboardEvent::create(eventNameForClipboardEvent(kind), dataTransfer.copyRef());
445
446 target->dispatchEvent(event);
447 bool noDefaultProcessing = event->defaultPrevented();
448 if (noDefaultProcessing && (kind == ClipboardEventKind::Copy || kind == ClipboardEventKind::Cut) && dataTransfer->pasteboard().hasData())
449 dataTransfer->commitToPasteboard(*Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(target->document().pageID())));
450
451 dataTransfer->makeInvalidForSecurity();
452
453 return !noDefaultProcessing;
454}
455
456// WinIE uses onbeforecut and onbeforepaste to enables the cut and paste menu items. They
457// also send onbeforecopy, apparently for symmetry, but it doesn't affect the menu items.
458// We need to use onbeforecopy as a real menu enabler because we allow elements that are not
459// normally selectable to implement copy/paste (like divs, or a document body).
460
461bool Editor::canDHTMLCut()
462{
463 if (m_document.selection().selection().isInPasswordField())
464 return false;
465
466 return !dispatchClipboardEvent(findEventTargetFromSelection(), ClipboardEventKind::BeforeCut);
467}

469bool Editor::canDHTMLCopy()

474}
475
476bool Editor::canDHTMLPaste()

478 return !dispatchClipboardEvent(findEventTargetFromSelection(), ClipboardEventKind::BeforePaste);
479}

486static HTMLImageElement* imageElementFromImageDocument(Document& document)
487{
488 if (!document.isImageDocument())
489 return nullptr;
490
491 HTMLElement* body = document.bodyOrFrameset();
492 if (!body)
493 return nullptr;
494
495 Node* node = body->firstChild();
496 if (!is<HTMLImageElement>(node))
497 return nullptr;
498 return downcast<HTMLImageElement>(node);
499}

522
523bool Editor::canDeleteRange(const SimpleRange& range) const
524{
525 if (!range.start.container->hasEditableStyle() || !range.end.container->hasEditableStyle())
526 return false;
527
528 if (range.collapsed()) {
529 // FIXME: We sometimes allow deletions at the start of editable roots, like when the caret is in an empty list item.
530 auto previous = VisiblePosition { makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.start) }.previous();
531 if (previous.isNull() || previous.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->rootEditableElement() != range.start.container->rootEditableElement())
532 return false;
533 }
534
535 return true;
536}

560bool Editor::deleteWithDirection(SelectionDirection direction, TextGranularity granularity, bool shouldAddToKillRing, bool isTypingAction)
561{
562 if (!canEdit())
563 return false;
564
565 if (m_document.selection().isRange()) {
566 if (isTypingAction) {
567 TypingCommand::deleteKeyPressed(document(), canSmartCopyOrDelete() ? TypingCommand::SmartDelete : 0, granularity);
568 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation();
569 } else {
570 if (shouldAddToKillRing)
571 addRangeToKillRing(*selectedRange(), KillRingInsertionMode::AppendText);
572 deleteSelectionWithSmartDelete(canSmartCopyOrDelete());
573 // Implicitly calls revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation().
574 }
575 } else {
576 TypingCommand::Options options = 0;
577 if (canSmartCopyOrDelete())
578 options |= TypingCommand::SmartDelete;
579 if (shouldAddToKillRing)
580 options |= TypingCommand::AddsToKillRing;
581 switch (direction) {
582 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
583 case SelectionDirection::Right:
584 TypingCommand::forwardDeleteKeyPressed(document(), options, granularity);
585 break;
586 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
587 case SelectionDirection::Left:
588 TypingCommand::deleteKeyPressed(document(), options, granularity);
589 break;
590 }
591 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation();
592 }
593
594 // FIXME: We should to move this down into deleteKeyPressed.
595 // clear the "start new kill ring sequence" setting, because it was set to true
596 // when the selection was updated by deleting the range
597 if (shouldAddToKillRing)
598 setStartNewKillRingSequence(false);
599
600 return true;
601}

665bool Editor::shouldInsertFragment(DocumentFragment& fragment, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& replacingDOMRange, EditorInsertAction givenAction)
666{
667 if (!client())
668 return false;
669
670 auto child = makeRefPtr(fragment.firstChild());
671 if (is<CharacterData>(child) && fragment.lastChild() == child)
672 return client()->shouldInsertText(downcast<CharacterData>(*child).data(), replacingDOMRange, givenAction);
673
674 return client()->shouldInsertNode(fragment, replacingDOMRange, givenAction);
675}
676
677void Editor::replaceSelectionWithFragment(DocumentFragment& fragment, SelectReplacement selectReplacement, SmartReplace smartReplace, MatchStyle matchStyle, EditAction editingAction, MailBlockquoteHandling mailBlockquoteHandling)
678{
679 VisibleSelection selection = m_document.selection().selection();
680 if (selection.isNone() || !selection.isContentEditable())
681 return;
682
683 AccessibilityReplacedText replacedText;
684 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && (editingAction == EditAction::Paste || editingAction == EditAction::Insert))
685 replacedText = AccessibilityReplacedText(selection);
686
687 OptionSet<ReplaceSelectionCommand::CommandOption> options { ReplaceSelectionCommand::PreventNesting, ReplaceSelectionCommand::SanitizeFragment };
688 if (selectReplacement == SelectReplacement::Yes)
689 options.add(ReplaceSelectionCommand::SelectReplacement);
690 if (smartReplace == SmartReplace::Yes)
691 options.add(ReplaceSelectionCommand::SmartReplace);
692 if (matchStyle == MatchStyle::Yes)
693 options.add(ReplaceSelectionCommand::MatchStyle);
694 if (mailBlockquoteHandling == MailBlockquoteHandling::IgnoreBlockquote)
695 options.add(ReplaceSelectionCommand::IgnoreMailBlockquote);
696
697 auto command = ReplaceSelectionCommand::create(document(), &fragment, options, editingAction);
698 command->apply();
699
700 m_imageElementsToLoadBeforeRevealingSelection.clear();
701 if (auto insertionRange = command->insertedContentRange())
702 m_imageElementsToLoadBeforeRevealingSelection = visibleImageElementsInRangeWithNonLoadedImages(*insertionRange);
703
704 if (m_imageElementsToLoadBeforeRevealingSelection.isEmpty())
705 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation();
706
707 selection = m_document.selection().selection();
708 if (selection.isInPasswordField())
709 return;
710
711 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && editingAction == EditAction::Paste) {
712 String text = AccessibilityObject::stringForVisiblePositionRange(command->visibleSelectionForInsertedText());
713 replacedText.postTextStateChangeNotification(document().existingAXObjectCache(), AXTextEditTypePaste, text, m_document.selection().selection());
714 command->composition()->setRangeDeletedByUnapply(replacedText.replacedRange());
715 }
716
717 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && editingAction == EditAction::Insert) {
718 String text = command->documentFragmentPlainText();
719 replacedText.postTextStateChangeNotification(document().existingAXObjectCache(), AXTextEditTypeInsert, text, m_document.selection().selection());
720 command->composition()->setRangeDeletedByUnapply(replacedText.replacedRange());
721 }
722
723 if (!isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
724 return;
725
726 auto nodeToCheck = makeRefPtr(selection.rootEditableElement());
727 if (!nodeToCheck)
728 return;
729
730 auto rangeToCheck = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*nodeToCheck);
731 if (auto request = SpellCheckRequest::create(resolveTextCheckingTypeMask(*nodeToCheck, { TextCheckingType::Spelling, TextCheckingType::Grammar }), TextCheckingProcessBatch, rangeToCheck, rangeToCheck, rangeToCheck))
732 m_spellChecker->requestCheckingFor(request.releaseNonNull());
733}

791
792bool Editor::hasBidiSelection() const
793{
794 if (m_document.selection().isNone())
795 return false;
796
797 RefPtr<Node> startNode;
798 if (m_document.selection().isRange()) {
799 startNode = m_document.selection().selection().start().downstream().deprecatedNode();
800 auto endNode = makeRefPtr(m_document.selection().selection().end().upstream().deprecatedNode());
801 if (enclosingBlock(startNode.get()) != enclosingBlock(endNode.get()))
802 return false;
803 } else
804 startNode = m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart().deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode();
805
806 if (!startNode)
807 return false;
808
809 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
810
811 auto renderer = startNode->renderer();
812 while (renderer && !is<RenderBlockFlow>(*renderer))
813 renderer = renderer->parent();
814
815 if (!renderer)
816 return false;
817
818 if (!renderer->style().isLeftToRightDirection())
819 return true;
820
821 return downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*renderer).containsNonZeroBidiLevel();
822}

824TriState Editor::selectionUnorderedListState() const
825{
826 if (m_document.selection().isCaret()) {
827 if (enclosingElementWithTag(m_document.selection().selection().start(), ulTag))
828 return TriState::True;

831 auto endNode = makeRefPtr(enclosingElementWithTag(m_document.selection().selection().end(), ulTag));
832 if (startNode && endNode && startNode == endNode)

836 return TriState::False;

954
955void Editor::applyStyle(RefPtr<EditingStyle>&& style, EditAction editingAction, ColorFilterMode colorFilterMode)
956{
957 if (!style)
958 return;
959
960 if (m_document.selection().isNone())
961 return;
962
963 String inputTypeName = inputTypeNameForEditingAction(editingAction);
964 String inputEventData = inputEventDataForEditingStyleAndAction(*style, editingAction);
965 auto element = makeRefPtr(m_document.selection().selection().rootEditableElement());
966
967 if (element && !dispatchBeforeInputEvent(*element, inputTypeName, inputEventData))
968 return;
969
970 if (m_document.selection().isNone())
971 return;
972
973 auto styleToApply = colorFilterMode == ColorFilterMode::InvertColor ? style->inverseTransformColorIfNeeded(*element) : style.releaseNonNull();
974 if (m_document.selection().isCaret())
975 computeAndSetTypingStyle(styleToApply, editingAction);
976 else
977 ApplyStyleCommand::create(document(), styleToApply.ptr(), editingAction)->apply();
978
979 if (client())
980 client()->didApplyStyle();
981 if (element)
982 dispatchInputEvent(*element, inputTypeName, inputEventData);
983}

1078static void notifyTextFromControls(Element* startRoot, Element* endRoot)
1079{
1080 auto startingTextControl = makeRefPtr(enclosingTextFormControl(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(startRoot)));
1081 auto endingTextControl = makeRefPtr(enclosingTextFormControl(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(endRoot)));
1082 if (startingTextControl)
1083 startingTextControl->didEditInnerTextValue();
1084 if (endingTextControl && startingTextControl != endingTextControl)
1085 endingTextControl->didEditInnerTextValue();
1086}
1087
1088static bool dispatchBeforeInputEvents(RefPtr<Element> startRoot, RefPtr<Element> endRoot, const AtomString& inputTypeName, const String& data = { }, RefPtr<DataTransfer>&& dataTransfer = nullptr, const Vector<RefPtr<StaticRange>>& targetRanges = { }, Event::IsCancelable cancelable = Event::IsCancelable::Yes)
1089{
1090 bool continueWithDefaultBehavior = true;
1091 if (startRoot)
1092 continueWithDefaultBehavior &= dispatchBeforeInputEvent(*startRoot, inputTypeName, data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges, cancelable);
1093 if (endRoot && endRoot != startRoot)
1094 continueWithDefaultBehavior &= dispatchBeforeInputEvent(*endRoot, inputTypeName, data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges, cancelable);
1095 return continueWithDefaultBehavior;
1096}
1097
1098static void dispatchInputEvents(RefPtr<Element> startRoot, RefPtr<Element> endRoot, const AtomString& inputTypeName, const String& data = { }, RefPtr<DataTransfer>&& dataTransfer = nullptr, const Vector<RefPtr<StaticRange>>& targetRanges = { })
1099{
1100 if (startRoot)
1101 dispatchInputEvent(*startRoot, inputTypeName, data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges);
1102 if (endRoot && endRoot != startRoot)
1103 dispatchInputEvent(*endRoot, inputTypeName, data, WTFMove(dataTransfer), targetRanges);
1104}
1105
1106bool Editor::willApplyEditing(CompositeEditCommand& command, Vector<RefPtr<StaticRange>>&& targetRanges) const
1107{
1108 if (!command.shouldDispatchInputEvents())
1109 return true;
1110
1111 auto composition = makeRefPtr(command.composition());
1112 if (!composition)
1113 return true;
1114
1115 if (command.isTopLevelCommand() && command.isTypingCommand() && document().view())
1116 m_prohibitScrollingDueToContentSizeChangesWhileTyping = document().view()->prohibitScrollingWhenChangingContentSizeForScope();
1117
1118 return dispatchBeforeInputEvents(composition->startingRootEditableElement(), composition->endingRootEditableElement(), command.inputEventTypeName(),
1119 command.inputEventData(), command.inputEventDataTransfer(), targetRanges, command.isBeforeInputEventCancelable() ? Event::IsCancelable::Yes : Event::IsCancelable::No);
1120}
1121
1122void Editor::appliedEditing(CompositeEditCommand& command)
1123{
1124 LOG(Editing, "Editor %p appliedEditing", this);
1125
1126 document().updateLayout();
1127
1128 ASSERT(command.composition());
1129 auto composition = makeRef(*command.composition());
1130 VisibleSelection newSelection(command.endingSelection());
1131
1132 notifyTextFromControls(composition->startingRootEditableElement(), composition->endingRootEditableElement());
1133
1134 if (command.isTopLevelCommand()) {
1135 // Don't clear the typing style with this selection change. We do those things elsewhere if necessary.
1136 OptionSet<FrameSelection::SetSelectionOption> options;
1137 if (command.isDictationCommand())
1138 options.add(FrameSelection::DictationTriggered);
1139
1140 changeSelectionAfterCommand(newSelection, options);
1141 }
1142
1143 if (command.shouldDispatchInputEvents())
1144 dispatchInputEvents(composition->startingRootEditableElement(), composition->endingRootEditableElement(), command.inputEventTypeName(), command.inputEventData(), command.inputEventDataTransfer());
1145
1146 if (command.isTopLevelCommand()) {
1147 updateEditorUINowIfScheduled();
1148
1149 m_alternativeTextController->respondToAppliedEditing(&command);
1150
1151 if (!command.preservesTypingStyle())
1152 m_document.selection().clearTypingStyle();
1153
1154 // Command will be equal to last edit command only in the case of typing
1155 if (m_lastEditCommand.get() == &command)
1156 ASSERT(command.isTypingCommand());
1157 else {
1158 // Only register a new undo command if the command passed in is
1159 // different from the last command
1160 m_lastEditCommand = &command;
1161 if (client())
1162 client()->registerUndoStep(m_lastEditCommand->ensureComposition());
1163 }
1164 respondToChangedContents(newSelection);
1165
1166 if (command.isTypingCommand())
1167 m_prohibitScrollingDueToContentSizeChangesWhileTyping = nullptr;
1168 }
1169}

1171bool Editor::willUnapplyEditing(const EditCommandComposition& composition) const

1176void Editor::unappliedEditing(EditCommandComposition& composition)
1177{

1180 notifyTextFromControls(composition.startingRootEditableElement(), composition.endingRootEditableElement());
1181

1189
1190 m_lastEditCommand = nullptr;
1191 if (auto* client = this->client())

1194}

1270
1271bool Editor::insertTextWithoutSendingTextEvent(const String& text, bool selectInsertedText, TextEvent* triggeringEvent)
1272{
1273 if (text.isEmpty())
1274 return false;
1275
1276 VisibleSelection selection = selectionForCommand(triggeringEvent);
1277 if (!selection.isContentEditable())
1278 return false;
1279
1280 if (!shouldInsertText(text, selection.toNormalizedRange(), EditorInsertAction::Typed))
1281 return true;
1282
1283 // FIXME: Should pass false to updateMarkersForWordsAffectedByEditing() to not remove markers if
1284 // a leading or trailing no-break space is being inserted. See <https://webkit.org/b/212098>.
1285 bool isStartOfNewWord = isSpaceOrNewline(selection.visibleStart().characterBefore());
1286 updateMarkersForWordsAffectedByEditing(isSpaceOrNewline(text[0]) || isStartOfNewWord);
1287
1288 bool shouldConsiderApplyingAutocorrection = false;
1289 if (text == " " || text == "\t")
1290 shouldConsiderApplyingAutocorrection = true;
1291
1292 if (text.length() == 1 && u_ispunct(text[0]) && !isAmbiguousBoundaryCharacter(text[0]))
1293 shouldConsiderApplyingAutocorrection = true;
1294
1295 bool autocorrectionWasApplied = shouldConsiderApplyingAutocorrection && m_alternativeTextController->applyAutocorrectionBeforeTypingIfAppropriate();
1296
1297 // Get the selection to use for the event that triggered this insertText.
1298 // If the event handler changed the selection, we may want to use a different selection
1299 // that is contained in the event target.
1300 selection = selectionForCommand(triggeringEvent);
1301 if (selection.isContentEditable()) {
1302 if (auto selectionStart = makeRefPtr(selection.start().deprecatedNode())) {
1303 Ref<Document> document(selectionStart->document());
1304
1305 // Insert the text
1306 if (triggeringEvent && triggeringEvent->isDictation())
1307 DictationCommand::insertText(document, text, triggeringEvent->dictationAlternatives(), selection);
1308 else {
1309 TypingCommand::Options options = 0;
1310 if (selectInsertedText)
1311 options |= TypingCommand::SelectInsertedText;
1312 if (autocorrectionWasApplied)
1313 options |= TypingCommand::RetainAutocorrectionIndicator;
1314 if (triggeringEvent && triggeringEvent->isAutocompletion())
1315 options |= TypingCommand::IsAutocompletion;
1316 TypingCommand::insertText(document, text, selection, options, triggeringEvent && triggeringEvent->isComposition() ? TypingCommand::TextCompositionFinal : TypingCommand::TextCompositionNone);
1317 }
1318
1319 // Reveal the current selection. Note that focus may have changed after insertion.
1320 // FIXME: Selection is allowed even if setIgnoreSelectionChanges(true). Ideally setIgnoreSelectionChanges()
1321 // should be moved from Editor to a page-level like object. If it must remain a frame-specific concept
1322 // then this code should conditionalize revealing selection on whether the ignoreSelectionChanges() bit
1323 // is set for the newly focused frame.
1324 if (client() && client()->shouldRevealCurrentSelectionAfterInsertion()) {
1325 if (auto* page = document->page())
1326 page->revealCurrentSelection();
1327 }
1328 }
1329 }
1330
1331 return true;
1332}
1333
1334bool Editor::insertLineBreak()
1335{
1336 if (!canEdit())
1337 return false;
1338
1339 if (!shouldInsertText("\n"_s, m_document.selection().selection().toNormalizedRange(), EditorInsertAction::Typed))
1340 return true;
1341
1342 VisiblePosition caret = m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart();
1343 bool alignToEdge = isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(caret);
1344 bool autocorrectionIsApplied = m_alternativeTextController->applyAutocorrectionBeforeTypingIfAppropriate();
1345 TypingCommand::insertLineBreak(document(), autocorrectionIsApplied ? TypingCommand::RetainAutocorrectionIndicator : 0);
1346 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation(alignToEdge ? ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded : ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded);
1347
1348 return true;
1349}
1350
1351bool Editor::insertParagraphSeparator()
1352{
1353 if (!canEdit())
1354 return false;
1355
1356 if (!canEditRichly())
1357 return insertLineBreak();
1358
1359 if (!shouldInsertText("\n"_s, m_document.selection().selection().toNormalizedRange(), EditorInsertAction::Typed))
1360 return true;
1361
1362 VisiblePosition caret = m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart();
1363 bool alignToEdge = isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(caret);
1364 bool autocorrectionIsApplied = m_alternativeTextController->applyAutocorrectionBeforeTypingIfAppropriate();
1365 TypingCommand::insertParagraphSeparator(document(), autocorrectionIsApplied ? TypingCommand::RetainAutocorrectionIndicator : 0);
1366 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation(alignToEdge ? ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded : ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded);
1367
1368 return true;
1369}

1371bool Editor::insertParagraphSeparatorInQuotedContent()
1372{
1373 // FIXME: Why is this missing calls to canEdit, canEditRichly, etc.?
1374 TypingCommand::insertParagraphSeparatorInQuotedContent(document());
1375 revealSelectionAfterEditingOperation();
1376 return true;
1377}

1417void Editor::performCutOrCopy(EditorActionSpecifier action)
1418{
1419 auto selection = selectedRange();
1420 willWriteSelectionToPasteboard(selection);
1421 if (action == CutAction) {
1422 if (!shouldDeleteRange(selection))
1423 return;
1424
1425 updateMarkersForWordsAffectedByEditing(true);
1426 }
1427
1428 if (enclosingTextFormControl(m_document.selection().selection().start()) || (selection && HTMLElement::isInsideImageOverlay(*selection)))
1429 Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(m_document.pageID()))->writePlainText(selectedTextForDataTransfer(), canSmartCopyOrDelete() ? Pasteboard::CanSmartReplace : Pasteboard::CannotSmartReplace);
1430 else {
1431 RefPtr<HTMLImageElement> imageElement;
1432 if (action == CopyAction)
1433 imageElement = imageElementFromImageDocument(document());
1434
1435 if (imageElement) {
1436#if !PLATFORM(WIN)
1437 writeImageToPasteboard(*Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(m_document.pageID())), *imageElement, document().url(), document().title());
1438#else
1439 // FIXME: Delete after <http://webkit.org/b/177618> lands.
1440 Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(m_document.pageID()))->writeImage(*imageElement, document().url(), document().title());
1441#endif
1442 } else {
1443#if !PLATFORM(WIN)
1444 writeSelectionToPasteboard(*Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(m_document.pageID())));
1445#else
1446 // FIXME: Delete after <http://webkit.org/b/177618> lands.
1447 Pasteboard::createForCopyAndPaste(PagePasteboardContext::create(m_document.pageID()))->writeSelection(*selection, canSmartCopyOrDelete(), *m_document.frame(), IncludeImageAltTextForDataTransfer);
1448#endif
1449 }
1450 }
1451
1452 didWriteSelectionToPasteboard();
1453 if (action == CutAction) {
1454 String text;
1455 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
1456 text = AccessibilityObject::stringForVisiblePositionRange(m_document.selection().selection());
1457 deleteSelectionWithSmartDelete(canSmartCopyOrDelete(), EditAction::Cut);
1458 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
1459 postTextStateChangeNotificationForCut(text, m_document.selection().selection());
1460 }
1461}

1878void Editor::setBaseWritingDirection(WritingDirection direction)
1879{
1880#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1881 if (inSameParagraph(m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart(), m_document.selection().selection().visibleEnd())
1882 && baseWritingDirectionForSelectionStart() == direction)
1883 return;
1884#endif
1885
1886 auto focusedElement = makeRefPtr(document().focusedElement());
1887 if (focusedElement && focusedElement->isTextField()) {
1888 if (direction == WritingDirection::Natural)
1889 return;
1890
1891 auto& focusedFormElement = downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*focusedElement);
1892 auto directionValue = direction == WritingDirection::LeftToRight ? "ltr" : "rtl";
1893 auto writingDirectionInputTypeName = inputTypeNameForEditingAction(EditAction::SetBlockWritingDirection);
1894 if (!dispatchBeforeInputEvent(focusedFormElement, writingDirectionInputTypeName, directionValue))
1895 return;
1896
1897 focusedFormElement.setAttributeWithoutSynchronization(dirAttr, directionValue);
1898 dispatchInputEvent(focusedFormElement, writingDirectionInputTypeName, directionValue);
1899 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
1900 return;
1901 }
1902
1903 auto style = MutableStyleProperties::create();
1904 style->setProperty(CSSPropertyDirection, direction == WritingDirection::LeftToRight ? "ltr" : direction == WritingDirection::RightToLeft ? "rtl" : "inherit", false);
1905 applyParagraphStyleToSelection(style.ptr(), EditAction::SetBlockWritingDirection);
1906}
1907
1908WritingDirection Editor::baseWritingDirectionForSelectionStart() const
1909{
1910 auto result = WritingDirection::LeftToRight;
1911
1912 Position pos = m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart().deepEquivalent();
1913 auto node = makeRefPtr(pos.deprecatedNode());
1914 if (!node)
1915 return result;
1916
1917 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
1918
1919 auto renderer = node->renderer();
1920 if (!renderer)
1921 return result;
1922
1923 if (!renderer->isRenderBlockFlow()) {
1924 renderer = renderer->containingBlock();
1925 if (!renderer)
1926 return result;
1927 }
1928
1929 switch (renderer->style().direction()) {
1930 case TextDirection::LTR:
1931 return WritingDirection::LeftToRight;
1932 case TextDirection::RTL:
1933 return WritingDirection::RightToLeft;
1934 }
1935
1936 return result;
1937}

1939void Editor::selectComposition()
1940{
1941 auto range = compositionRange();
1942 if (!range)
1943 return;
1944
1945 // The composition can start inside a composed character sequence, so we have to override checks.
1946 // See <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15781>
1947 VisibleSelection selection;
1948 selection.setWithoutValidation(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range->start), makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range->end));
1949 m_document.selection().setSelection(selection, { });
1950}

1959void Editor::confirmOrCancelCompositionAndNotifyClient()
1960{
1961 if (!hasComposition())
1962 return;
1963

1966 return;

1969 return;

1974 editorClient->respondToChangedSelection(frame.get());
1975 editorClient->discardedComposition(frame.get());
1976 }

2001
2002class SetCompositionScope {
2003public:
2004 SetCompositionScope(Document& document)
2005 : m_document(RefPtr(&document))
2006 , m_typingGestureIndicator(*document.frame())
2007 {
2008 m_document->editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(true);
2009 }
2010
2011 ~SetCompositionScope()
2012 {
2013 m_document->editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(false);
2014 if (auto* editorClient = m_document->editor().client())
2015 editorClient->didUpdateComposition();
2016 }
2017
2018 RefPtr<Document> m_document;
2019 UserTypingGestureIndicator m_typingGestureIndicator;
2020};
2021
2022void Editor::setComposition(const String& text, SetCompositionMode mode)
2023{
2024 ASSERT(mode == ConfirmComposition || mode == CancelComposition);
2025 SetCompositionScope setCompositionScope(m_document);
2026
2027 if (mode == CancelComposition)
2028 ASSERT(text == emptyString());
2029 else
2030 selectComposition();
2031
2032 m_compositionNode = nullptr;
2033 m_customCompositionUnderlines.clear();
2034 m_customCompositionHighlights.clear();
2035
2036 if (m_document.selection().isNone())
2037 return;
2038
2039 // Always delete the current composition before inserting the finalized composition text if we're confirming our composition.
2040 // Our default behavior (if the beforeinput event is not prevented) is to insert the finalized composition text back in.
2041 // We pass TypingCommand::TextCompositionPending here to indicate that we are deleting the pending composition.
2042 if (mode != CancelComposition)
2043 TypingCommand::deleteSelection(document(), 0, TypingCommand::TextCompositionPending);
2044
2045 insertTextForConfirmedComposition(text);
2046
2047 if (auto* target = document().focusedElement())
2048 target->dispatchEvent(CompositionEvent::create(eventNames().compositionendEvent, document().windowProxy(), text));
2049
2050 if (mode == CancelComposition) {
2051 // An open typing command that disagrees about current selection would cause issues with typing later on.
2052 TypingCommand::closeTyping(m_document);
2053 }
2054}
2055
2056void Editor::setComposition(const String& text, const Vector<CompositionUnderline>& underlines, const Vector<CompositionHighlight>& highlights, unsigned selectionStart, unsigned selectionEnd)
2057{
2058 SetCompositionScope setCompositionScope(m_document);
2059
2060 // Updates styles before setting selection for composition to prevent
2061 // inserting the previous composition text into text nodes oddly.
2062 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46868
2063 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
2064
2065 selectComposition();
2066
2067 if (m_document.selection().isNone())
2068 return;
2069
2070 String originalText = selectedText();
2071 bool isStartingToRecomposeExistingRange = !text.isEmpty() && selectionStart < selectionEnd && !hasComposition();
2072 if (isStartingToRecomposeExistingRange) {
2073 // We pass TypingCommand::TextCompositionFinal here to indicate that we are removing composition text that has been finalized.
2074 TypingCommand::deleteSelection(document(), 0, TypingCommand::TextCompositionFinal);
2075 const VisibleSelection& currentSelection = m_document.selection().selection();
2076 if (currentSelection.isRange()) {
2077 // If deletion was prevented, then we need to collapse the selection to the end so that the original text will not be recomposed.
2078 m_document.selection().setSelection({ currentSelection.end(), currentSelection.end() });
2079 }
2080 }
2081
2082#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2083 client()->startDelayingAndCoalescingContentChangeNotifications();
2084#endif
2085
2086 auto target = makeRefPtr(document().focusedElement());
2087 if (target) {
2088 // Dispatch an appropriate composition event to the focused node.
2089 // We check the composition status and choose an appropriate composition event since this
2090 // function is used for three purposes:
2091 // 1. Starting a new composition.
2092 // Send a compositionstart and a compositionupdate event when this function creates
2093 // a new composition node, i.e.
2094 // m_compositionNode == 0 && !text.isEmpty().
2095 // Sending a compositionupdate event at this time ensures that at least one
2096 // compositionupdate event is dispatched.
2097 // 2. Updating the existing composition node.
2098 // Send a compositionupdate event when this function updates the existing composition
2099 // node, i.e. m_compositionNode != 0 && !text.isEmpty().
2100 // 3. Canceling the ongoing composition.
2101 // Send a compositionend event when function deletes the existing composition node, i.e.
2102 // m_compositionNode != 0 && test.isEmpty().
2103 RefPtr<CompositionEvent> event;
2104 if (!m_compositionNode) {
2105 // We should send a compositionstart event only when the given text is not empty because this
2106 // function doesn't create a composition node when the text is empty.
2107 if (!text.isEmpty()) {
2108 target->dispatchEvent(CompositionEvent::create(eventNames().compositionstartEvent, document().windowProxy(), originalText));
2109 event = CompositionEvent::create(eventNames().compositionupdateEvent, document().windowProxy(), text);
2110 }
2111 } else if (!text.isEmpty())
2112 event = CompositionEvent::create(eventNames().compositionupdateEvent, document().windowProxy(), text);
2113
2114 if (event)
2115 target->dispatchEvent(*event);
2116 }
2117
2118 // If text is empty, then delete the old composition here. If text is non-empty, InsertTextCommand::input
2119 // will delete the old composition with an optimized replace operation.
2120 if (text.isEmpty()) {
2121 TypingCommand::deleteSelection(document(), TypingCommand::PreventSpellChecking, TypingCommand::TextCompositionPending);
2122 if (target)
2123 target->dispatchEvent(CompositionEvent::create(eventNames().compositionendEvent, document().windowProxy(), text));
2124 }
2125
2126 m_compositionNode = nullptr;
2127 m_customCompositionUnderlines.clear();
2128 m_customCompositionHighlights.clear();
2129
2130 if (!text.isEmpty()) {
2131 TypingCommand::insertText(document(), text, TypingCommand::SelectInsertedText | TypingCommand::PreventSpellChecking, TypingCommand::TextCompositionPending);
2132
2133 // Find out what node has the composition now.
2134 Position base = m_document.selection().selection().base().downstream();
2135 Position extent = m_document.selection().selection().extent();
2136 auto baseNode = makeRefPtr(base.deprecatedNode());
2137 unsigned baseOffset = base.deprecatedEditingOffset();
2138 auto extentNode = makeRefPtr(extent.deprecatedNode());
2139 unsigned extentOffset = extent.deprecatedEditingOffset();
2140
2141 if (is<Text>(baseNode) && baseNode == extentNode && baseOffset + text.length() == extentOffset) {
2142 m_compositionNode = static_pointer_cast<Text>(baseNode);
2143 m_compositionStart = baseOffset;
2144 m_compositionEnd = extentOffset;
2145 m_customCompositionUnderlines = underlines;
2146 for (auto& underline : m_customCompositionUnderlines) {
2147 underline.startOffset += baseOffset;
2148 underline.endOffset += baseOffset;
2149 }
2150 m_customCompositionHighlights = highlights;
2151 for (auto& highlight : m_customCompositionHighlights) {
2152 highlight.startOffset += baseOffset;
2153 highlight.endOffset += baseOffset;
2154 }
2155
2156 if (auto renderer = baseNode->renderer()) {
2157#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
2158 if (auto lineLayout = LayoutIntegration::LineLayout::containing(*renderer))
2159 lineLayout->flow().ensureLineBoxes();
2160#endif
2161 renderer->repaint();
2162 }
2163
2164 unsigned start = std::min(baseOffset + selectionStart, extentOffset);
2165 unsigned end = std::min(std::max(start, baseOffset + selectionEnd), extentOffset);
2166 auto range = SimpleRange { { *baseNode, start }, { *baseNode, end } };
2167 m_document.selection().setSelectedRange(range, Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::No);
2168 }
2169 }
2170
2171#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2172 client()->stopDelayingAndCoalescingContentChangeNotifications();
2173#endif
2174}

2205
2206void Editor::advanceToNextMisspelling(bool startBeforeSelection)
2207{
2208 Ref<Document> protectedDocument(m_document);
2209
2210 // The basic approach is to search in two phases: from the selection end to the end of the document, and
2211 // then we wrap and search from the document start to (approximately) where we started.
2212
2213 // Start at the end of the selection, search to edge of document.
2214 // Starting at the selection end makes repeated "check spelling" commands work.
2215 VisibleSelection selection(m_document.selection().selection());
2216 auto spellingSearchRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document());
2217
2218 bool startedWithSelection = false;
2219 if (selection.start().deprecatedNode()) {
2220 startedWithSelection = true;
2221 if (startBeforeSelection) {
2222 // Match AppKit's rule: Start 1 character before the selection.
2223 auto start = selection.visibleStart();
2224 auto beforeStart = start.previous();
2225 if (beforeStart.isNotNull())
2226 start = beforeStart;
2227 spellingSearchRange.start = *makeBoundaryPoint(start);
2228 } else
2229 spellingSearchRange.start = *makeBoundaryPoint(selection.visibleEnd());
2230 }
2231
2232 auto position = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(spellingSearchRange.start);
2233 if (!isEditablePosition(position)) {
2234 // This shouldn't happen in very often because the Spelling menu items aren't enabled unless the
2235 // selection is editable.
2236 // This can happen in Mail for a mix of non-editable and editable content (like Stationary),
2237 // when spell checking the whole document before sending the message.
2238 // In that case the document might not be editable, but there are editable pockets that need to be spell checked.
2239
2240 position = VisiblePosition(firstEditablePositionAfterPositionInRoot(position, document().documentElement())).deepEquivalent();
2241 if (position.isNull())
2242 return;
2243
2244 if (auto point = makeBoundaryPoint(position.parentAnchoredEquivalent()))
2245 spellingSearchRange.start = *point;
2246 startedWithSelection = false; // won't need to wrap
2247 }
2248
2249 // topNode defines the whole range we want to operate on
2250 auto topNode = makeRefPtr(highestEditableRoot(position));
2251 if (topNode)
2252 spellingSearchRange.end = makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*topNode);
2253
2254 // If spellingSearchRange starts in the middle of a word, advance to the next word so we start checking
2255 // at a word boundary. Going back by one char and then forward by a word does the trick.
2256 if (startedWithSelection) {
2257 auto oneBeforeStart = VisiblePosition(makeContainerOffsetPosition(spellingSearchRange.start)).previous();
2258 if (oneBeforeStart.isNotNull())
2259 spellingSearchRange.start = *makeBoundaryPoint(endOfWord(oneBeforeStart));
2260 // else we were already at the start of the editable node
2261 }
2262
2263 if (spellingSearchRange.collapsed())
2264 return; // nothing to search in
2265
2266 // Get the spell checker if it is available
2267 if (!client())
2268 return;
2269
2270 // We go to the end of our first range instead of the start of it, just to be sure
2271 // we don't get foiled by any word boundary problems at the start. It means we might
2272 // do a tiny bit more searching.
2273 auto searchEndAfterWrap = spellingSearchRange.end;
2274
2275 TextCheckingHelper::MisspelledWord misspelledWord;
2276 TextCheckingHelper::UngrammaticalPhrase ungrammaticalPhrase;
2277 auto grammarSearchRange = spellingSearchRange;
2278
2279 if (unifiedTextCheckerEnabled()) {
2280 auto foundItem = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), spellingSearchRange).findFirstMisspelledWordOrUngrammaticalPhrase(isGrammarCheckingEnabled());
2281 if (auto word = WTF::get_if<TextCheckingHelper::MisspelledWord>(foundItem))
2282 misspelledWord = WTFMove(*word);
2283 else
2284 ungrammaticalPhrase = WTF::get<TextCheckingHelper::UngrammaticalPhrase>(WTFMove(foundItem));
2285 } else {
2286 misspelledWord = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), spellingSearchRange).findFirstMisspelledWord();
2287
2288 if (!misspelledWord.word.isEmpty()) {
2289 // Stop looking at start of next misspelled word
2290 CharacterIterator characterIterator(grammarSearchRange);
2291 characterIterator.advance(misspelledWord.offset);
2292 grammarSearchRange.end = characterIterator.range().start;
2293 }
2294
2295 if (isGrammarCheckingEnabled())
2296 ungrammaticalPhrase = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), grammarSearchRange).findFirstUngrammaticalPhrase();
2297 }
2298
2299 // If we found neither bad grammar nor a misspelled word, wrap and try again (but don't bother if we started at the beginning of the
2300 // block rather than at a selection).
2301 if (startedWithSelection && misspelledWord.word.isEmpty() && ungrammaticalPhrase.phrase.isEmpty()) {
2302 if (topNode)
2303 spellingSearchRange.start = makeBoundaryPointBeforeNodeContents(*topNode);
2304 spellingSearchRange.end = searchEndAfterWrap;
2305
2306 if (unifiedTextCheckerEnabled()) {
2307 auto foundItem = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), spellingSearchRange).findFirstMisspelledWordOrUngrammaticalPhrase(isGrammarCheckingEnabled());
2308 if (auto word = WTF::get_if<TextCheckingHelper::MisspelledWord>(foundItem))
2309 misspelledWord = WTFMove(*word);
2310 else
2311 ungrammaticalPhrase = WTF::get<TextCheckingHelper::UngrammaticalPhrase>(WTFMove(foundItem));
2312 } else {
2313 misspelledWord = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), spellingSearchRange).findFirstMisspelledWord();
2314
2315 grammarSearchRange = spellingSearchRange;
2316 if (!misspelledWord.word.isEmpty()) {
2317 // Stop looking at start of next misspelled word
2318 CharacterIterator characterIterator(grammarSearchRange);
2319 characterIterator.advance(misspelledWord.offset);
2320 grammarSearchRange.end = characterIterator.range().start;
2321 }
2322
2323 if (isGrammarCheckingEnabled())
2324 ungrammaticalPhrase = TextCheckingHelper(*client(), grammarSearchRange).findFirstUngrammaticalPhrase();
2325 }
2326 }
2327
2328 if (!ungrammaticalPhrase.phrase.isEmpty()) {
2329 // We found bad grammar. Since we only searched for bad grammar up to the first misspelled word, the bad grammar
2330 // takes precedence and we ignore any potential misspelled word. Select the grammar detail, update the spelling
2331 // panel, and store a marker so we draw the green squiggle later.
2332
2333 ASSERT(ungrammaticalPhrase.phrase.length() > 0);
2334 ASSERT(ungrammaticalPhrase.detail.range.length > 0);
2335
2336 // FIXME 4859190: This gets confused with doubled punctuation at the end of a paragraph.
2337 auto badGrammarRange = resolveCharacterRange(grammarSearchRange, { ungrammaticalPhrase.offset + ungrammaticalPhrase.detail.range.location, ungrammaticalPhrase.detail.range.length });
2338 m_document.selection().setSelection(VisibleSelection(badGrammarRange));
2339 m_document.selection().revealSelection();
2340
2341 client()->updateSpellingUIWithGrammarString(ungrammaticalPhrase.phrase, ungrammaticalPhrase.detail);
2342 addMarker(badGrammarRange, DocumentMarker::Grammar, ungrammaticalPhrase.detail.userDescription);
2343 } else if (!misspelledWord.word.isEmpty()) {
2344 // We found a misspelling, but not any earlier bad grammar. Select the misspelling, update the spelling panel, and store
2345 // a marker so we draw the red squiggle later.
2346
2347 auto misspellingRange = resolveCharacterRange(spellingSearchRange, { misspelledWord.offset, misspelledWord.word.length() });
2348 m_document.selection().setSelection(VisibleSelection(misspellingRange));
2349 m_document.selection().revealSelection();
2350
2351 client()->updateSpellingUIWithMisspelledWord(misspelledWord.word);
2352 addMarker(misspellingRange, DocumentMarker::Spelling);
2353 }
2354}

2358String Editor::misspelledWordAtCaretOrRange(Node* clickedNode) const
2359{
2360 if (!isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled() || !clickedNode || !isSpellCheckingEnabledFor(clickedNode))
2361 return String();
2362
2363 VisibleSelection selection = m_document.selection().selection();
2364 if (!selection.isContentEditable() || selection.isNone())
2365 return String();
2366
2367 VisibleSelection wordSelection(selection.base());
2368 wordSelection.expandUsingGranularity(TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
2369 auto wordRange = wordSelection.toNormalizedRange();
2370 if (!wordRange)
2371 return String();
2372
2373 // In compliance with GTK+ applications, additionally allow to provide suggestions when the current
2374 // selection exactly match the word selection.
2375 if (selection.isRange() && *wordRange != selection.toNormalizedRange())
2376 return String();
2377
2378 String word = plainText(*wordRange);
2379 if (word.isEmpty() || !client())
2380 return String();
2381
2382 int wordLength = word.length();
2383 int misspellingLocation = -1;
2384 int misspellingLength = 0;
2385 textChecker()->checkSpellingOfString(word, &misspellingLocation, &misspellingLength);
2386
2387 return misspellingLength == wordLength ? word : String();
2388}

2390String Editor::misspelledSelectionString() const
2391{
2392 String selectedString = selectedText();
2393 int length = selectedString.length();
2394 if (!length || !client())
2395 return String();
2396
2397 int misspellingLocation = -1;
2398 int misspellingLength = 0;
2399 textChecker()->checkSpellingOfString(selectedString, &misspellingLocation, &misspellingLength);
2400
2401 // The selection only counts as misspelled if the selected text is exactly one misspelled word
2402 if (misspellingLength != length)
2403 return String();
2404
2405 // Update the spelling panel to be displaying this error (whether or not the spelling panel is on screen).
2406 // This is necessary to make a subsequent call to [NSSpellChecker ignoreWord:inSpellDocumentWithTag:] work
2407 // correctly; that call behaves differently based on whether the spelling panel is displaying a misspelling
2408 // or a grammar error.
2409 client()->updateSpellingUIWithMisspelledWord(selectedString);
2410
2411 return selectedString;

2481
2482void Editor::markMisspellingsAfterTypingToWord(const VisiblePosition& wordStart, const VisibleSelection& selectionAfterTyping, bool doReplacement)
2483{
2484 Ref<Document> protectedDocument(m_document);
2485
2486 if (platformDrivenTextCheckerEnabled())
2487 return;
2488
2489#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2490 UNUSED_PARAM(selectionAfterTyping);
2491 UNUSED_PARAM(doReplacement);
2492 OptionSet<TextCheckingType> textCheckingOptions;
2493 if (isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
2494 textCheckingOptions.add(TextCheckingType::Spelling);
2495 if (!textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Spelling))
2496 return;
2497
2498 auto adjacentWords = VisibleSelection(startOfWord(wordStart, LeftWordIfOnBoundary), endOfWord(wordStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary));
2499 auto adjacentWordRange = adjacentWords.toNormalizedRange();
2500 markAllMisspellingsAndBadGrammarInRanges(textCheckingOptions, adjacentWordRange, adjacentWordRange, adjacentWordRange);
2501#else
2502#if !USE(AUTOMATIC_TEXT_REPLACEMENT)
2503 UNUSED_PARAM(doReplacement);
2504#endif
2505
2506 if (unifiedTextCheckerEnabled()) {
2507 m_alternativeTextController->applyPendingCorrection(selectionAfterTyping);
2508
2509 OptionSet<TextCheckingType> textCheckingOptions;
2510
2511 if (isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
2512 textCheckingOptions.add(TextCheckingType::Spelling);
2513
2514#if USE(AUTOMATIC_TEXT_REPLACEMENT)
2515 if (doReplacement
2516 && (isAutomaticQuoteSubstitutionEnabled()
2517 || isAutomaticLinkDetectionEnabled()
2518 || isAutomaticDashSubstitutionEnabled()
2519 || isAutomaticTextReplacementEnabled()
2520 || (textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Spelling) && isAutomaticSpellingCorrectionEnabled())))
2521 textCheckingOptions.add(TextCheckingType::Replacement);
2522#endif
2523 if (!textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Spelling) && !textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Replacement))
2524 return;
2525
2526 if (isGrammarCheckingEnabled())
2527 textCheckingOptions.add(TextCheckingType::Grammar);
2528
2529 auto sentenceStart = startOfSentence(wordStart);
2530 auto sentenceEnd = endOfSentence(wordStart);
2531 VisibleSelection fullSentence(sentenceStart, sentenceEnd);
2532 auto fullSentenceRange = fullSentence.toNormalizedRange();
2533 if (!fullSentenceRange)
2534 return;
2535
2536 auto spellCheckingStart = wordStart;
2537 auto spellCheckingEnd = wordStart;
2538
2539 // FIXME: The following logic doesn't handle adding spelling markers due to retro sentence corrections when an
2540 // incorrectly spelled range is separated from the start of the current word by a text node inside an element
2541 // with spellcheck disabled. To fix this, we need to refactor markAllMisspellingsAndBadGrammarInRanges so that
2542 // it can handle a list of spelling ranges, alongside the grammar range.
2543 while (sentenceStart < spellCheckingStart) {
2544 auto previousPosition = spellCheckingStart.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
2545 if (previousPosition.isNull() || previousPosition == spellCheckingStart)
2546 break;
2547
2548 auto* container = previousPosition.deepEquivalent().downstream().containerNode();
2549 if (auto* containerElement = is<Element>(container) ? downcast<Element>(container) : container->parentElement()) {
2550 if (!containerElement->isSpellCheckingEnabled())
2551 break;
2552 }
2553
2554 spellCheckingStart = previousPosition;
2555 }
2556
2557 while (spellCheckingEnd < sentenceEnd) {
2558 auto nextPosition = spellCheckingEnd.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
2559 if (nextPosition.isNull() || nextPosition == spellCheckingEnd)
2560 break;
2561
2562 if (auto containerElement = makeRefPtr(nextPosition.deepEquivalent().upstream().containerOrParentElement())) {
2563 if (!containerElement->isSpellCheckingEnabled())
2564 break;
2565 }
2566
2567 spellCheckingEnd = nextPosition;
2568 }
2569
2570 auto spellCheckingRange = VisibleSelection(spellCheckingStart, spellCheckingEnd).toNormalizedRange();
2571 if (!spellCheckingRange)
2572 return;
2573
2574 auto adjacentWordRange = intersection(VisibleSelection(startOfWord(wordStart, LeftWordIfOnBoundary), endOfWord(wordStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary)).toNormalizedRange(), fullSentenceRange);
2575 if (!adjacentWordRange)
2576 return;
2577
2578 // The spelling and grammar markers in these ranges are recomputed. This is because typing a word may
2579 // cause any other part of the current sentence to lose or gain spelling correction markers, due to
2580 // sentence retro correction. As such, we expand the spell checking range to encompass as much of the
2581 // full sentence as we can, respecting boundaries where spellchecking is disabled.
2582 removeMarkers(*fullSentenceRange, DocumentMarker::Grammar);
2583 removeMarkers(*spellCheckingRange, DocumentMarker::Spelling);
2584 markAllMisspellingsAndBadGrammarInRanges(textCheckingOptions, spellCheckingRange, adjacentWordRange, fullSentenceRange);
2585 return;
2586 }
2587
2588 if (!isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
2589 return;
2590
2591 // Check spelling of one word
2592 auto misspellingRange = markMisspellings(VisibleSelection(startOfWord(wordStart, LeftWordIfOnBoundary), endOfWord(wordStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary)));
2593
2594 // Autocorrect the misspelled word.
2595 if (!misspellingRange)
2596 return;
2597
2598 // Get the misspelled word.
2599 String autocorrectedString = textChecker()->getAutoCorrectSuggestionForMisspelledWord(plainText(*misspellingRange));
2600
2601 // If autocorrected word is non empty, replace the misspelled word by this word.
2602 if (!autocorrectedString.isEmpty()) {
2603 VisibleSelection newSelection(*misspellingRange);
2604 if (newSelection != m_document.selection().selection()) {
2605 if (!m_document.selection().shouldChangeSelection(newSelection))
2606 return;
2607 m_document.selection().setSelection(newSelection);
2608 }
2609
2610 if (!m_document.editor().shouldInsertText(autocorrectedString, misspellingRange, EditorInsertAction::Typed))
2611 return;
2612 m_document.editor().replaceSelectionWithText(autocorrectedString, SelectReplacement::No, SmartReplace::No, EditAction::Insert);
2613
2614 // Reset the charet one character further.
2615 m_document.selection().moveTo(m_document.selection().selection().end());
2616 m_document.selection().modify(FrameSelection::AlterationMove, SelectionDirection::Forward, TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity);
2617 }
2618
2619 if (!isGrammarCheckingEnabled())
2620 return;
2621
2622 // Check grammar of entire sentence
2623 markBadGrammar(VisibleSelection(startOfSentence(wordStart), endOfSentence(wordStart)));
2624#endif
2625}
2626
2627std::optional<SimpleRange> Editor::markMisspellingsOrBadGrammar(const VisibleSelection& selection, bool checkSpelling)
2628{
2629#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2630 // This function is called with a selection already expanded to word boundaries.
2631 // Might be nice to assert that here.
2632
2633 // This function is used only for as-you-type checking, so if that's off we do nothing. Note that
2634 // grammar checking can only be on if spell checking is also on.
2635 if (!isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
2636 return std::nullopt;
2637
2638 auto searchRange = selection.toNormalizedRange();
2639 if (!searchRange)
2640 return std::nullopt;
2641
2642 // If we're not in an editable node, bail.
2643 Node& editableNode = searchRange->startContainer();
2644 if (!editableNode.hasEditableStyle())
2645 return std::nullopt;
2646
2647 if (!isSpellCheckingEnabledFor(&editableNode))
2648 return std::nullopt;
2649
2650 // Get the spell checker if it is available
2651 if (!client())
2652 return std::nullopt;
2653
2654 TextCheckingHelper checker(*client(), *searchRange);
2655 if (checkSpelling)
2656 return checker.markAllMisspelledWords();
2657 if (isGrammarCheckingEnabled())
2658 checker.markAllUngrammaticalPhrases();
2659 return std::nullopt;
2660#else
2661 UNUSED_PARAM(selection);
2662 UNUSED_PARAM(checkSpelling);
2663 return std::nullopt;
2664#endif
2665}
2666
2667bool Editor::isSpellCheckingEnabledFor(Node* node) const
2668{
2669 if (!node)
2670 return false;
2671 auto element = makeRefPtr(is<Element>(*node) ? downcast<Element>(node) : node->parentElement());
2672 if (!element)
2673 return false;
2674 if (element->isInUserAgentShadowTree()) {
2675 if (auto textControl = makeRefPtr(enclosingTextFormControl(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(element.get()))))
2676 return textControl->isSpellCheckingEnabled();
2677 }
2678 return element->isSpellCheckingEnabled();
2679}
2680
2681bool Editor::isSpellCheckingEnabledInFocusedNode() const
2682{

2695
2696void Editor::markAllMisspellingsAndBadGrammarInRanges(OptionSet<TextCheckingType> textCheckingOptions, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& spellingRange, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& automaticReplacementRange, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& grammarRange)
2697{
2698 if (platformDrivenTextCheckerEnabled())
2699 return;
2700
2701 ASSERT(unifiedTextCheckerEnabled());
2702
2703 // There shouldn't be pending autocorrection at this moment.
2704 ASSERT(!m_alternativeTextController->hasPendingCorrection());
2705
2706 bool shouldMarkGrammar = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Grammar);
2707 bool shouldShowCorrectionPanel = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::ShowCorrectionPanel);
2708
2709 // This function is called with selections already expanded to word boundaries.
2710 if (!client() || !spellingRange || (shouldMarkGrammar && !grammarRange))
2711 return;
2712
2713 // If we're not in an editable node, bail.
2714 auto editableNode = makeRef(spellingRange->startContainer());
2715 if (!editableNode->hasEditableStyle())
2716 return;
2717
2718 if (!isSpellCheckingEnabledFor(editableNode.ptr()))
2719 return;
2720
2721 auto& rangeToCheck = shouldMarkGrammar ? *grammarRange : *spellingRange;
2722 TextCheckingParagraph paragraphToCheck(rangeToCheck);
2723 if (paragraphToCheck.isEmpty())
2724 return;
2725
2726 bool asynchronous = m_document.settings().asynchronousSpellCheckingEnabled() && !shouldShowCorrectionPanel;
2727
2728 // In asynchronous mode, we intentionally check paragraph-wide sentence.
2729 auto resolvedOptions = resolveTextCheckingTypeMask(editableNode, textCheckingOptions);
2730 auto& paragraphRange = paragraphToCheck.paragraphRange();
2731 auto& checkingRange = asynchronous ? paragraphRange : rangeToCheck;
2732 auto& textReplacementRange = automaticReplacementRange ? *automaticReplacementRange : rangeToCheck;
2733 auto request = SpellCheckRequest::create(resolvedOptions, TextCheckingProcessIncremental, checkingRange, textReplacementRange, paragraphRange);
2734 if (!request)
2735 return;
2736
2737 if (asynchronous) {
2738 m_spellChecker->requestCheckingFor(request.releaseNonNull());
2739 return;
2740 }
2741
2742 Vector<TextCheckingResult> results;
2743 checkTextOfParagraph(*textChecker(), paragraphToCheck.text(), resolvedOptions, results, m_document.selection().selection());
2744 markAndReplaceFor(request.releaseNonNull(), results);
2745}
2746
2747static bool isAutomaticTextReplacementType(TextCheckingType type)
2748{
2749 switch (type) {
2750 case TextCheckingType::None:
2751 case TextCheckingType::Spelling:
2752 case TextCheckingType::Grammar:
2753 return false;
2754 case TextCheckingType::Link:
2755 case TextCheckingType::Quote:
2756 case TextCheckingType::Dash:
2757 case TextCheckingType::Replacement:
2758 case TextCheckingType::Correction:
2759 case TextCheckingType::ShowCorrectionPanel:
2760 return true;
2761 }
2762 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2763 return false;
2764}

2770
2771static void correctSpellcheckingPreservingTextCheckingParagraph(TextCheckingParagraph& paragraph, const SimpleRange& rangeToReplace, const String& replacement, CharacterRange resultCharacterRange)
2772{
2773 auto scopeNode = makeRef(downcast<ContainerNode>(paragraph.paragraphRange().startContainer().rootNode()));
2774 auto paragraphCharacterRange = characterRange(makeBoundaryPointBeforeNodeContents(scopeNode), paragraph.paragraphRange());
2775
2776 SpellingCorrectionCommand::create(rangeToReplace, replacement)->apply();
2777
2778 // TextCheckingParagraph may be orphaned after SpellingCorrectionCommand mutated DOM.
2779 // See <rdar://10305315>, http://webkit.org/b/89526.
2780
2781 paragraphCharacterRange.length += replacement.length() - resultCharacterRange.length;
2782 auto newParagraphRange = resolveCharacterRange(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(scopeNode), paragraphCharacterRange);
2783 auto spellCheckingRange = resolveCharacterRange(newParagraphRange, { resultCharacterRange.location, replacement.length() });
2784 paragraph = TextCheckingParagraph(spellCheckingRange, spellCheckingRange, newParagraphRange);
2785}
2786
2787void Editor::markAndReplaceFor(const SpellCheckRequest& request, const Vector<TextCheckingResult>& results)
2788{
2789 Ref<Document> protectedDocument(m_document);
2790
2791 auto textCheckingOptions = request.data().checkingTypes();
2792 TextCheckingParagraph paragraph(request.checkingRange(), request.automaticReplacementRange(), request.paragraphRange());
2793
2794 // FIXME: Mark this const once MSVC bug is fixed: <https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/316713/msvc-cant-compile-webkits-optionsetcontainsany.html>.
2795 bool shouldPerformReplacement = textCheckingOptions.containsAny({ TextCheckingType::Quote, TextCheckingType::Dash, TextCheckingType::Replacement });
2796 bool shouldMarkSpelling = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Spelling);
2797 bool shouldMarkGrammar = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Grammar);
2798 bool shouldMarkLink = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Link);
2799 bool shouldShowCorrectionPanel = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::ShowCorrectionPanel);
2800 bool shouldCheckForCorrection = shouldShowCorrectionPanel || textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Correction);
2801#if !USE(AUTOCORRECTION_PANEL)
2802 ASSERT(!shouldShowCorrectionPanel);
2803#endif
2804
2805 // Expand the range to encompass entire paragraphs, since text checking needs that much context.
2806 uint64_t selectionOffset = 0;
2807 bool useAmbiguousBoundaryOffset = false;
2808 bool selectionChanged = false;
2809 bool restoreSelectionAfterChange = false;
2810
2811 if (shouldPerformReplacement || shouldMarkSpelling || shouldCheckForCorrection) {
2812 if (m_document.selection().isCaret()) {
2813 // Attempt to save the caret position so we can restore it later if needed
2814 Position caretPosition = m_document.selection().selection().end();
2815 selectionOffset = paragraph.offsetTo(caretPosition).releaseReturnValue();
2816 restoreSelectionAfterChange = true;
2817 if (selectionOffset > 0 && selectionOffset <= paragraph.text().length() && isAmbiguousBoundaryCharacter(paragraph.text()[selectionOffset - 1]))
2818 useAmbiguousBoundaryOffset = true;
2819 }
2820 }
2821
2822 int offsetDueToReplacement = 0;
2823
2824 for (unsigned i = 0; i < results.size(); i++) {
2825 auto spellingRangeEndOffset = paragraph.checkingEnd() + offsetDueToReplacement;
2826 TextCheckingType resultType = results[i].type;
2827 auto resultLocation = results[i].range.location + offsetDueToReplacement;
2828 auto resultLength = results[i].range.length;
2829 auto resultEndLocation = resultLocation + resultLength;
2830 auto automaticReplacementStartLocation = paragraph.automaticReplacementStart();
2831 auto automaticReplacementEndLocation = automaticReplacementStartLocation + paragraph.automaticReplacementLength() + offsetDueToReplacement;
2832 const String& replacement = results[i].replacement;
2833 bool resultEndsAtAmbiguousBoundary = useAmbiguousBoundaryOffset && selectionOffset - 1 <= resultEndLocation;
2834
2835 // Only mark misspelling if:
2836 // 1. Current text checking isn't done for autocorrection, in which case shouldMarkSpelling is false.
2837 // 2. Result falls within spellingRange.
2838 // 3. The word in question doesn't end at an ambiguous boundary. For instance, we would not mark
2839 // "wouldn'" as misspelled right after apostrophe is typed.
2840 if (shouldMarkSpelling && !shouldShowCorrectionPanel && resultType == TextCheckingType::Spelling
2841 && resultLocation >= paragraph.checkingStart() && resultEndLocation <= spellingRangeEndOffset && !resultEndsAtAmbiguousBoundary) {
2842 ASSERT(resultLength > 0);
2843 auto misspellingRange = paragraph.subrange({ resultLocation, resultLength });
2844 if (!m_alternativeTextController->isSpellingMarkerAllowed(misspellingRange))
2845 continue;
2846 addMarker(misspellingRange, DocumentMarker::Spelling, replacement);
2847 } else if (shouldMarkGrammar && resultType == TextCheckingType::Grammar && paragraph.checkingRangeCovers({ resultLocation, resultLength })) {
2848 ASSERT(resultLength > 0);
2849 for (auto& detail : results[i].details) {
2850 ASSERT(detail.range.length > 0);
2851 if (paragraph.checkingRangeCovers({ resultLocation + detail.range.location, detail.range.length })) {
2852 auto badGrammarRange = paragraph.subrange({ resultLocation + detail.range.location, detail.range.length });
2853 addMarker(badGrammarRange, DocumentMarker::Grammar, detail.userDescription);
2854 }
2855 }
2856 } else if (automaticReplacementStartLocation <= resultEndLocation && resultEndLocation <= automaticReplacementEndLocation
2857 && isAutomaticTextReplacementType(resultType)) {
2858 // In this case the result range just has to touch the automatic replacement range, so we can handle replacing non-word text such as punctuation.
2859 ASSERT(resultLength > 0);
2860
2861 if (shouldShowCorrectionPanel && (resultEndLocation < automaticReplacementEndLocation
2862 || (resultType != TextCheckingType::Replacement && resultType != TextCheckingType::Correction)))
2863 continue;
2864
2865 // Apply replacement if:
2866 // 1. The replacement length is non-zero.
2867 // 2. The result doesn't end at an ambiguous boundary.
2868 // (FIXME: this is required until 6853027 is fixed and text checking can do this for us
2869 bool doReplacement = replacement.length() > 0 && !resultEndsAtAmbiguousBoundary;
2870 auto rangeToReplace = paragraph.subrange({ resultLocation, resultLength });
2871
2872 // Adding links should be done only immediately after they are typed.
2873 if (resultType == TextCheckingType::Link && selectionOffset != resultEndLocation + 1)
2874 continue;
2875
2876 if (!(shouldPerformReplacement || shouldCheckForCorrection || shouldMarkLink) || !doReplacement)
2877 continue;
2878
2879 String replacedString = plainText(rangeToReplace);
2880 bool existingMarkersPermitReplacement = m_alternativeTextController->processMarkersOnTextToBeReplacedByResult(results[i], rangeToReplace, replacedString);
2881 if (!existingMarkersPermitReplacement)
2882 continue;
2883
2884 if (shouldShowCorrectionPanel) {
2885 if (resultEndLocation == automaticReplacementEndLocation) {
2886 // We only show the correction panel on the last word.
2887 m_alternativeTextController->show(rangeToReplace, replacement);
2888 break;
2889 }
2890 // If this function is called for showing correction panel, we ignore other correction or replacement.
2891 continue;
2892 }
2893
2894 VisibleSelection selectionToReplace(rangeToReplace);
2895 if (selectionToReplace != m_document.selection().selection()) {
2896 if (!m_document.selection().shouldChangeSelection(selectionToReplace))
2897 continue;
2898 }
2899
2900 if (resultType == TextCheckingType::Link) {
2901 m_document.selection().setSelection(selectionToReplace);
2902 selectionChanged = true;
2903 restoreSelectionAfterChange = false;
2904 if (canEditRichly())
2905 CreateLinkCommand::create(document(), replacement)->apply();
2906 } else if (canEdit() && shouldInsertText(replacement, rangeToReplace, EditorInsertAction::Typed)) {
2907 correctSpellcheckingPreservingTextCheckingParagraph(paragraph, rangeToReplace, replacement, { resultLocation, resultLength });
2908
2909 if (AXObjectCache* cache = document().existingAXObjectCache()) {
2910 if (auto root = makeRefPtr(m_document.selection().selection().rootEditableElement()))
2911 cache->postNotification(root.get(), AXObjectCache::AXAutocorrectionOccured);
2912 }
2913
2914 // Skip all other results for the replaced text.
2915 while (i + 1 < results.size() && results[i + 1].range.location + offsetDueToReplacement <= resultLocation)
2916 i++;
2917
2918 selectionChanged = true;
2919 offsetDueToReplacement += replacement.length() - resultLength;
2920 if (resultLocation < selectionOffset)
2921 selectionOffset += replacement.length() - resultLength;
2922
2923 if (resultType == TextCheckingType::Correction) {
2924 auto replacementRange = paragraph.subrange({ resultLocation, replacement.length() });
2925 m_alternativeTextController->recordAutocorrectionResponse(AutocorrectionResponse::Accepted, replacedString, replacementRange);
2926
2927 // Add a marker so that corrections can easily be undone and won't be re-corrected.
2928 m_alternativeTextController->markCorrection(replacementRange, replacedString);
2929 }
2930 }
2931 }
2932 }
2933
2934 if (selectionChanged) {
2935 TextCheckingParagraph extendedParagraph(WTFMove(paragraph));
2936 // Restore the caret position if we have made any replacements
2937 extendedParagraph.expandRangeToNextEnd();
2938 if (restoreSelectionAfterChange && selectionOffset <= extendedParagraph.rangeLength()) {
2939 auto selectionRange = extendedParagraph.subrange({ 0, selectionOffset });
2940 m_document.selection().moveTo(makeContainerOffsetPosition(selectionRange.end), Affinity::Downstream);
2941 } else {
2942 // If this fails for any reason, the fallback is to go one position beyond the last replacement
2943 m_document.selection().moveTo(m_document.selection().selection().end());
2944 m_document.selection().modify(FrameSelection::AlterationMove, SelectionDirection::Forward, TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity);
2945 }
2946 }
2947}
