3001
3002void Editor::updateMarkersForWordsAffectedByEditing(bool doNotRemoveIfSelectionAtWordBoundary)
3003{
3004 if (!document().markers().hasMarkers())
3005 return;
3006
3007 if (!m_alternativeTextController->shouldRemoveMarkersUponEditing() && (!textChecker() || textChecker()->shouldEraseMarkersAfterChangeSelection(TextCheckingType::Spelling)))
3008 return;
3009
3010 // We want to remove the markers from a word if an editing command will change the word. This can happen in one of
3011 // several scenarios:
3012 // 1. Insert in the middle of a word.
3013 // 2. Appending non whitespace at the beginning of word.
3014 // 3. Appending non whitespace at the end of word.
3015 // Note that, appending only whitespaces at the beginning or end of word won't change the word, so we don't need to
3016 // remove the markers on that word.
3017 // Of course, if current selection is a range, we potentially will edit two words that fall on the boundaries of
3018 // selection, and remove words between the selection boundaries.
3019 //
3020 VisiblePosition startOfSelection = m_document.selection().selection().start();
3021 VisiblePosition endOfSelection = m_document.selection().selection().end();
3022 if (startOfSelection.isNull())
3023 return;
3024 // First word is the word that ends after or on the start of selection.
3025 VisiblePosition startOfFirstWord = startOfWord(startOfSelection, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
3026 VisiblePosition endOfFirstWord = endOfWord(startOfSelection, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
3027 // Last word is the word that begins before or on the end of selection
3028 VisiblePosition startOfLastWord = startOfWord(endOfSelection, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3029 VisiblePosition endOfLastWord = endOfWord(endOfSelection, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3030
3031 if (startOfFirstWord.isNull()) {
3032 startOfFirstWord = startOfWord(startOfSelection, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3033 endOfFirstWord = endOfWord(startOfSelection, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3034 }
3035
3036 if (endOfLastWord.isNull()) {
3037 startOfLastWord = startOfWord(endOfSelection, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
3038 endOfLastWord = endOfWord(endOfSelection, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
3039 }
3040
3041 auto originalEndOfFirstWord = endOfFirstWord;
3042 auto originalStartOfLastWord = startOfLastWord;
3043
3044 // If doNotRemoveIfSelectionAtWordBoundary is true, and first word ends at the start of selection,
3045 // we choose next word as the first word.
3046 if (doNotRemoveIfSelectionAtWordBoundary && endOfFirstWord == startOfSelection) {
3047 startOfFirstWord = nextWordPosition(startOfFirstWord);
3048 endOfFirstWord = endOfWord(startOfFirstWord, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3049 if (startOfFirstWord == originalStartOfLastWord)
3050 return;
3051 }
3052
3053 // If doNotRemoveIfSelectionAtWordBoundary is true, and last word begins at the end of selection,
3054 // we choose previous word as the last word.
3055 if (doNotRemoveIfSelectionAtWordBoundary && startOfLastWord == endOfSelection) {
3056 startOfLastWord = previousWordPosition(startOfLastWord);
3057 endOfLastWord = endOfWord(startOfLastWord, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
3058 if (endOfLastWord == originalEndOfFirstWord)
3059 return;
3060 }
3061
3062 if (startOfFirstWord.isNull() || endOfFirstWord.isNull() || startOfLastWord.isNull() || endOfLastWord.isNull())
3063 return;
3064
3065 // Now we remove markers on everything between startOfFirstWord and endOfLastWord.
3066 // However, if an autocorrection change a single word to multiple words, we want to remove correction mark from all the
3067 // resulted words even we only edit one of them. For example, assuming autocorrection changes "avantgarde" to "avant
3068 // garde", we will have CorrectionIndicator marker on both words and on the whitespace between them. If we then edit garde,
3069 // we would like to remove the marker from word "avant" and whitespace as well. So we need to get the continous range of
3070 // of marker that contains the word in question, and remove marker on that whole range.
3071 auto wordRange = *makeSimpleRange(startOfFirstWord, endOfLastWord);
3072
3073 for (auto* marker : document().markers().markersInRange(wordRange, DocumentMarker::DictationAlternatives))
3074 m_alternativeTextController->removeDictationAlternativesForMarker(*marker);
3075
3076 OptionSet<DocumentMarker::MarkerType> markerTypesToRemove {
3077 DocumentMarker::CorrectionIndicator,
3078 DocumentMarker::DictationAlternatives,
3079 DocumentMarker::SpellCheckingExemption,
3080 DocumentMarker::Spelling,
3081#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3082 DocumentMarker::Grammar,
3083#endif
3084 };
3085 removeMarkers(wordRange, markerTypesToRemove, RemovePartiallyOverlappingMarker::Yes);
3086 document().markers().clearDescriptionOnMarkersIntersectingRange(wordRange, DocumentMarker::Replacement);
3087}

3144bool Editor::getCompositionSelection(unsigned& selectionStart, unsigned& selectionEnd) const
3145{

3147 return false;
3148 const VisibleSelection& selection = m_document.selection().selection();

3165
3166void Editor::transpose()
3167{
3168 if (!canEdit())
3169 return;
3170
3171 VisibleSelection selection = m_document.selection().selection();
3172 if (!selection.isCaret())
3173 return;
3174
3175 // Make a selection that goes back one character and forward two characters.
3176 VisiblePosition caret = selection.visibleStart();
3177 VisiblePosition next = isEndOfParagraph(caret) ? caret : caret.next();
3178 VisiblePosition previous = next.previous();
3179 if (next == previous)
3180 return;
3181 previous = previous.previous();
3182 if (!inSameParagraph(next, previous))
3183 return;
3184 auto range = makeSimpleRange(previous, next);
3185 if (!range)
3186 return;
3187 VisibleSelection newSelection(*range);
3188
3189 // Transpose the two characters.
3190 String text = plainText(*range);
3191 if (text.length() != 2)
3192 return;
3193 String transposed = text.right(1) + text.left(1);
3194
3195 // Select the two characters.
3196 if (newSelection != m_document.selection().selection()) {
3197 if (!m_document.selection().shouldChangeSelection(newSelection))
3198 return;
3199 m_document.selection().setSelection(newSelection);
3200 }
3201
3202 // Insert the transposed characters.
3203 if (!shouldInsertText(transposed, newSelection.firstRange(), EditorInsertAction::Typed))
3204 return;
3205 replaceSelectionWithText(transposed, SelectReplacement::No, SmartReplace::No, EditAction::Insert);
3206}

3213void Editor::addTextToKillRing(const String& text, KillRingInsertionMode mode)
3214{
3215 if (m_shouldStartNewKillRingSequence)
3216 killRing().startNewSequence();
3217
3218 m_shouldStartNewKillRingSequence = false;
3219
3220 // If the kill was from a backwards motion, prepend to the kill ring.
3221 // This will ensure that alternating forward and backward kills will
3222 // build up the original string in the kill ring without permuting it.
3223 switch (mode) {
3224 case KillRingInsertionMode::PrependText:
3225 killRing().prepend(text);
3226 break;
3227 case KillRingInsertionMode::AppendText:
3228 killRing().append(text);
3229 break;
3230 }

3249void Editor::changeSelectionAfterCommand(const VisibleSelection& newSelection, OptionSet<FrameSelection::SetSelectionOption> options)
3250{
3251 Ref<Document> protectedDocument(m_document);
3252
3253 // If the new selection is orphaned, then don't update the selection.
3254 if (newSelection.start().isOrphan() || newSelection.end().isOrphan())
3255 return;
3256
3257 // If there is no selection change, don't bother sending shouldChangeSelection, but still call setSelection,
3258 // because there is work that it must do in this situation.
3259 // The old selection can be invalid here and calling shouldChangeSelection can produce some strange calls.
3260 // See <rdar://problem/5729315> Some shouldChangeSelectedDOMRange contain Ranges for selections that are no longer valid
3261 bool selectionDidNotChangeDOMPosition = newSelection == m_document.selection().selection();
3262 if (selectionDidNotChangeDOMPosition || m_document.selection().shouldChangeSelection(newSelection))
3263 m_document.selection().setSelection(newSelection, options);
3264
3265 // Some editing operations change the selection visually without affecting its position within the DOM.
3266 // For example when you press return in the following (the caret is marked by ^):
3267 // <div contentEditable="true"><div>^Hello</div></div>
3268 // WebCore inserts <div><br></div> *before* the current block, which correctly moves the paragraph down but which doesn't
3269 // change the caret's DOM position (["hello", 0]). In these situations the above FrameSelection::setSelection call
3270 // does not call EditorClient::respondToChangedSelection(), which, on the Mac, sends selection change notifications and
3271 // starts a new kill ring sequence, but we want to do these things (matches AppKit).
3272#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3273 // FIXME: Should suppress selection change notifications during a composition change <https://webkit.org/b/38830>
3274 if (m_ignoreSelectionChanges)
3275 return;
3276#endif
3277 if (selectionDidNotChangeDOMPosition && client())
3278 client()->respondToChangedSelection(m_document.frame());
3279}

3305{

3307 return nullptr;

3358IntRect Editor::firstRectForRange(const SimpleRange& range) const
3359{

3363

3489template<typename T> static auto& start(T& range, FindOptions options)
3490{
3491 return options.contains(Backwards) ? range.end : range.start;
3492}

3495{

3499static BoundaryPoint makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(Node& node, FindOptions options)
3500{
3501 return options.contains(Backwards) ? makeBoundaryPointBeforeNodeContents(node) : makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(node);
3502}
3503
3504static std::optional<BoundaryPoint> makeBoundaryPointAfterNode(Node& node, FindOptions options)
3505{
3506 return options.contains(Backwards) ? makeBoundaryPointBeforeNode(node) : makeBoundaryPointAfterNode(node);
3507}
3508
3509static SimpleRange collapseIfRootsDiffer(SimpleRange&& range)
3510{
3511 // FIXME: This helps correct results in some cases involving shadow trees. But we can incorrectly find a string with middle characters in an input element and first and last characters outside it.
3512 return &range.start.container->rootNode() == &range.end.container->rootNode()
3513 ? WTFMove(range) : SimpleRange { range.start, range.start };
3514}
3515
3516std::optional<SimpleRange> Editor::rangeOfString(const String& target, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& referenceRange, FindOptions options)
3517{
3518 if (target.isEmpty())
3519 return std::nullopt;
3520
3521 // Start from an edge of the reference range, if there's a reference range that's not in shadow content. Which edge
3522 // is used depends on whether we're searching forward or backward, and whether startInSelection is set.
3523
3524 bool startInReferenceRange = referenceRange && options.contains(StartInSelection);
3525 auto shadowTreeRoot = referenceRange ? referenceRange->startContainer().containingShadowRoot() : nullptr;
3526
3527 auto searchRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document());
3528 if (referenceRange)
3529 start(searchRange, options) = startInReferenceRange ? start(*referenceRange, options) : end(*referenceRange, options);
3530 if (shadowTreeRoot)
3531 end(searchRange, options) = makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*shadowTreeRoot, options);
3532 auto resultRange = collapseIfRootsDiffer(findPlainText(searchRange, target, options));
3533
3534 // If we started in the reference range and the found range exactly matches the reference range, find again.
3535 // Build a selection with the found range to remove collapsed whitespace.
3536 // Compare ranges instead of selection objects to ignore the way that the current selection was made.
3537 if (startInReferenceRange && VisibleSelection(resultRange).toNormalizedRange() == referenceRange) {
3538 searchRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document());
3539 start(searchRange, options) = end(*referenceRange, options);
3540 if (shadowTreeRoot)
3541 end(searchRange, options) = makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*shadowTreeRoot, options);
3542 resultRange = collapseIfRootsDiffer(findPlainText(searchRange, target, options));
3543 }
3544
3545 // If nothing was found in the shadow tree, search in main content following the shadow tree.
3546 if (resultRange.collapsed() && shadowTreeRoot) {
3547 searchRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document());
3548 if (auto host = shadowTreeRoot->shadowHost())
3549 start(searchRange, options) = *makeBoundaryPointAfterNode(*host, options);
3550 resultRange = collapseIfRootsDiffer(findPlainText(searchRange, target, options));
3551 }
3552
3553 // If we didn't find anything and we're wrapping, search again in the entire document (this will
3554 // redundantly re-search the area already searched in some cases).
3555 if (resultRange.collapsed() && options.contains(WrapAround)) {
3556 resultRange = collapseIfRootsDiffer(findPlainText(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document()), target, options));
3557 // We used to return false here if we ended up with the same range that we started with
3558 // (e.g., the reference range was already the only instance of this text). But we decided that
3559 // this should be a success case instead, so we'll just fall through in that case.
3560 }
3561
3562 return resultRange.collapsed() ? std::nullopt : std::make_optional(resultRange);
3563}
3564
3565static bool isFrameInRange(Frame& frame, const SimpleRange& range)
3566{
3567 for (auto* ownerElement = frame.ownerElement(); ownerElement; ownerElement = ownerElement->document().ownerElement()) {
3568 if (&ownerElement->document() == &range.start.document())
3569 return intersects<ComposedTree>(range, *ownerElement);
3570 }
3571 return false;
3572}
3573
3574unsigned Editor::countMatchesForText(const String& target, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& range, FindOptions options, unsigned limit, bool markMatches, Vector<SimpleRange>* matches)
3575{
3576 if (target.isEmpty())
3577 return 0;
3578
3579 std::optional<SimpleRange> searchRange;
3580 if (range) {
3581 if (&range->start.document() == &document())
3582 searchRange = *range;
3583 else if (!isFrameInRange(*m_document.frame(), *range))
3584 return 0;
3585 }
3586 if (!searchRange)
3587 searchRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(document());
3588
3589 auto originalEnd = searchRange->end;
3590
3591 unsigned matchCount = 0;
3592 do {
3593 auto resultRange = findPlainText(*searchRange, target, options - Backwards);
3594 if (resultRange.collapsed()) {
3595 if (!resultRange.start.container->isInShadowTree())
3596 break;
3597
3598 searchRange->start = makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*resultRange.start.container->shadowHost());
3599 searchRange->end = originalEnd;
3600 continue;
3601 }
3602
3603 ++matchCount;
3604 if (matches)
3605 matches->append(resultRange);
3606
3607 if (markMatches)
3608 addMarker(resultRange, DocumentMarker::TextMatch);
3609
3610 // Stop looking if we hit the specified limit. A limit of 0 means no limit.
3611 if (limit > 0 && matchCount >= limit)
3612 break;
3613
3614 // Set the new start for the search range to be the end of the previous result range.
3615 // There is no need to use VisiblePosition here: findPlainText will use TextIterator to go over visible text nodes.
3616 searchRange->start = WTFMove(resultRange.end);
3617
3618 if (searchRange->collapsed()) {
3619 if (auto shadowTreeRoot = searchRange->start.container->containingShadowRoot())
3620 searchRange->end = makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*shadowTreeRoot);
3621 }
3622 } while (true);
3623
3624 return matchCount;
3625}

3676
3677static Vector<SimpleRange> scanForTelephoneNumbers(const SimpleRange& range)
3678{
3679 // Don't scan for phone numbers inside editable regions.
3680 if (auto startNode = makeRef(range.startContainer()); startNode->hasEditableStyle())
3681 return { };
3682
3683 if (HTMLElement::isInsideImageOverlay(range))
3684 return { };
3685
3686 auto text = plainText(range);
3687 Vector<SimpleRange> result;
3688 unsigned length = text.length();
3689 unsigned scannerPosition = 0;
3690 int relativeStartPosition = 0;
3691 int relativeEndPosition = 0;
3692 auto characters = StringView { text }.upconvertedCharacters();
3693 while (scannerPosition < length && TelephoneNumberDetector::find(&characters[scannerPosition], length - scannerPosition, &relativeStartPosition, &relativeEndPosition)) {
3694 ASSERT(scannerPosition + relativeEndPosition <= length);
3695 result.append(resolveCharacterRange(range, CharacterRange(scannerPosition + relativeStartPosition, relativeEndPosition - relativeStartPosition)));
3696 scannerPosition += relativeEndPosition;
3697 }
3698 return result;
3699}
3700
3701static std::optional<SimpleRange> extendSelection(const SimpleRange& range, unsigned charactersToExtend)
3702{
3703 auto start = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.start);
3704 auto end = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.end);
3705 for (unsigned i = 0; i < charactersToExtend; ++i) {
3706 start = start.previous(Character);
3707 end = end.next(Character);
3708 }
3709 return makeSimpleRange(start, end);
3710}
3711
3712void Editor::scanSelectionForTelephoneNumbers()
3713{
3714 // FIXME: Why is it helpful here to check client for null?
3715 if (!shouldDetectTelephoneNumbers() || !client())
3716 return;
3717
3718 m_detectedTelephoneNumberRanges.clear();
3719
3720 auto notifyController = makeScopeExit([&] {
3721 if (auto* page = m_document.page())
3722 page->servicesOverlayController().selectedTelephoneNumberRangesChanged();
3723 });
3724
3725 auto selection = m_document.selection().selection();
3726 if (!selection.isRange())
3727 return;
3728
3729 auto selectedRange = selection.firstRange();
3730 if (!selectedRange)
3731 return;
3732
3733 // Extend the range a few characters in each direction to detect incompletely selected phone numbers.
3734 constexpr unsigned charactersToExtend = 15;
3735 auto extendedRange = extendSelection(*selectedRange, charactersToExtend);
3736 if (!extendedRange)
3737 return;
3738
3739 for (auto& range : scanForTelephoneNumbers(*extendedRange)) {
3740 // FIXME: Why do we do this unconditionally instead of when only when it overlaps the selection?
3741 addMarker(range, DocumentMarker::TelephoneNumber);
3742
3743 // Only consider ranges with a detected telephone number if they overlap with the selection.
3744 if (intersects<ComposedTree>(range, *selectedRange))
3745 m_detectedTelephoneNumberRanges.append(range);
3746 }
3747}

3758
3759void Editor::editorUIUpdateTimerFired()
3760{
3761 VisibleSelection oldSelection = m_oldSelectionForEditorUIUpdate;
3762
3763 m_alternativeTextController->stopPendingCorrection(oldSelection);
3764
3765 bool isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled = this->isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled();
3766 bool isContinuousGrammarCheckingEnabled = isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled && isGrammarCheckingEnabled();
3767 if (isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled) {
3768 VisibleSelection newAdjacentWords;
3769 VisibleSelection newSelectedSentence;
3770 bool caretBrowsing = m_document.settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
3771 if (m_document.selection().selection().isContentEditable() || caretBrowsing) {
3772 VisiblePosition newStart(m_document.selection().selection().visibleStart());
3773#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3774 newAdjacentWords = VisibleSelection(startOfWord(newStart, LeftWordIfOnBoundary), endOfWord(newStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary));
3775#else
3776 // If this bug gets fixed, this PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) code could be removed:
3777 // <rdar://problem/7259611> Word boundary code on iPhone gives different results than desktop
3778 EWordSide startWordSide = LeftWordIfOnBoundary;
3779 UChar32 c = newStart.characterBefore();
3780 // FIXME: VisiblePosition::characterAfter() and characterBefore() do not emit newlines the same
3781 // way as TextIterator, so we do an isStartOfParagraph check here.
3782 if (isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace || isStartOfParagraph(newStart)) {
3783 startWordSide = RightWordIfOnBoundary;
3784 }
3785 newAdjacentWords = VisibleSelection(startOfWord(newStart, startWordSide), endOfWord(newStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary));
3786#endif // !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3787 if (isContinuousGrammarCheckingEnabled)
3788 newSelectedSentence = VisibleSelection(startOfSentence(newStart), endOfSentence(newStart));
3789 }
3790
3791 // When typing we check spelling elsewhere, so don't redo it here.
3792 // If this is a change in selection resulting from a delete operation,
3793 // oldSelection may no longer be in the document.
3794 if (m_editorUIUpdateTimerShouldCheckSpellingAndGrammar && oldSelection.isContentEditable() && oldSelection.start().deprecatedNode() && oldSelection.start().anchorNode()->isConnected()) {
3795 VisiblePosition oldStart(oldSelection.visibleStart());
3796 VisibleSelection oldAdjacentWords = VisibleSelection(startOfWord(oldStart, LeftWordIfOnBoundary), endOfWord(oldStart, RightWordIfOnBoundary));
3797 if (oldAdjacentWords != newAdjacentWords) {
3798 if (isContinuousGrammarCheckingEnabled) {
3799 VisibleSelection oldSelectedSentence = VisibleSelection(startOfSentence(oldStart), endOfSentence(oldStart));
3800 markMisspellingsAndBadGrammar(oldAdjacentWords, oldSelectedSentence != newSelectedSentence, oldSelectedSentence);
3801 } else
3802 markMisspellingsAndBadGrammar(oldAdjacentWords, false, oldAdjacentWords);
3803 }
3804 }
3805
3806 if (!textChecker() || textChecker()->shouldEraseMarkersAfterChangeSelection(TextCheckingType::Spelling)) {
3807 if (auto wordRange = newAdjacentWords.toNormalizedRange())
3808 removeMarkers(*wordRange, DocumentMarker::Spelling);
3809 }
3810 if (!textChecker() || textChecker()->shouldEraseMarkersAfterChangeSelection(TextCheckingType::Grammar)) {
3811 if (auto sentenceRange = newSelectedSentence.toNormalizedRange())
3812 removeMarkers(*sentenceRange, DocumentMarker::Grammar);
3813 }
3814 }
3815
3816 // When continuous spell checking is off, existing markers disappear after the selection changes.
3817 if (!isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled)
3818 document().markers().removeMarkers(DocumentMarker::Spelling);
3819 if (!isContinuousGrammarCheckingEnabled)
3820 document().markers().removeMarkers(DocumentMarker::Grammar);
3821
3822 if (!m_editorUIUpdateTimerWasTriggeredByDictation)
3823 m_alternativeTextController->respondToChangedSelection(oldSelection);
3824
3825 m_oldSelectionForEditorUIUpdate = m_document.selection().selection();
3826
3827#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
3828 notifyClientOfAttachmentUpdates();
3829#endif
3830}
3831
3832static RefPtr<Node> findFirstMarkable(Node* startingNode)
3833{
3834 auto node = makeRefPtr(startingNode);
3835 while (node) {
3836 {
3837 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
3838 if (!node->renderer())
3839 return nullptr;
3840 if (node->renderer()->isTextOrLineBreak())
3841 return node;
3842 }
3843 if (is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*node) && downcast<Element>(*node).isTextField())
3844 node = downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*node).visiblePositionForIndex(1).deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode();
3845 else if (node->firstChild())
3846 node = node->firstChild();
3847 else
3848 node = node->nextSibling();
3849 }
3850
3851 return nullptr;
3852}

3854bool Editor::selectionStartHasMarkerFor(DocumentMarker::MarkerType markerType, int from, int length) const
3855{
3856 auto node = findFirstMarkable(m_document.selection().selection().start().deprecatedNode());
3857 if (!node)
3858 return false;
3859
3860 unsigned int startOffset = static_cast<unsigned int>(from);
3861 unsigned int endOffset = static_cast<unsigned int>(from + length);
3862 Vector<RenderedDocumentMarker*> markers = document().markers().markersFor(*node);
3863 for (auto* marker : markers) {

3865 return true;

3871OptionSet<TextCheckingType> Editor::resolveTextCheckingTypeMask(const Node& rootEditableElement, OptionSet<TextCheckingType> textCheckingOptions)
3872{
3873#if USE(AUTOMATIC_TEXT_REPLACEMENT) && !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3874 bool onlyAllowsTextReplacement = false;
3875 if (auto host = makeRefPtr(rootEditableElement.shadowHost()))
3876 onlyAllowsTextReplacement = is<HTMLInputElement>(host) && downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*host).isSpellcheckDisabledExceptTextReplacement();
3877 if (onlyAllowsTextReplacement)
3878 textCheckingOptions = textCheckingOptions & TextCheckingType::Replacement;
3879#else
3880 UNUSED_PARAM(rootEditableElement);
3881#endif
3882
3883 bool shouldMarkSpelling = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Spelling);
3884 bool shouldMarkGrammar = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Grammar);
3885#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3886 bool shouldShowCorrectionPanel = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::ShowCorrectionPanel);
3887 bool shouldCheckForCorrection = shouldShowCorrectionPanel || textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Correction);
3888#endif
3889
3890 OptionSet<TextCheckingType> checkingTypes;
3891 if (shouldMarkSpelling)
3892 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Spelling);
3893 if (shouldMarkGrammar)
3894 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Grammar);
3895#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3896 if (shouldCheckForCorrection)
3897 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Correction);
3898 if (shouldShowCorrectionPanel)
3899 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::ShowCorrectionPanel);
3900
3901#if USE(AUTOMATIC_TEXT_REPLACEMENT)
3902 bool shouldPerformReplacement = textCheckingOptions.contains(TextCheckingType::Replacement);
3903 if (shouldPerformReplacement) {
3904 if (!onlyAllowsTextReplacement) {
3905 if (isAutomaticLinkDetectionEnabled())
3906 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Link);
3907 if (isAutomaticQuoteSubstitutionEnabled())
3908 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Quote);
3909 if (isAutomaticDashSubstitutionEnabled())
3910 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Dash);
3911 if (shouldMarkSpelling && isAutomaticSpellingCorrectionEnabled())
3912 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Correction);
3913 }
3914 if (isAutomaticTextReplacementEnabled())
3915 checkingTypes.add(TextCheckingType::Replacement);
3916 }
3917#endif
3918#endif // !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3919
3920 return checkingTypes;
3921}

3923static bool candidateWouldReplaceText(const VisibleSelection& selection)
3924{
3925 // If the character behind the caret in the current selection is anything but a space or a newline then we should
3926 // replace the whole current word with the candidate.
3927 UChar32 characterAfterSelection, characterBeforeSelection, twoCharacterBeforeSelection = 0;
3928 charactersAroundPosition(selection.visibleStart(), characterAfterSelection, characterBeforeSelection, twoCharacterBeforeSelection);
3929 return !(characterBeforeSelection == '\0' || characterBeforeSelection == '\n' || characterBeforeSelection == ' ');
3930}

3977static Vector<TextList> editableTextListsAtPositionInDescendingOrder(const Position& position)
3978{
3979 auto startContainer = makeRefPtr(position.containerNode());
3980 if (!startContainer)
3981 return { };
3982
3983 auto* editableRoot = highestEditableRoot(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(startContainer.get()));
3984 if (!editableRoot)
3985 return { };
3986
3987 Vector<Ref<HTMLElement>> enclosingLists;
3988 for (auto& ancestor : ancestorsOfType<HTMLElement>(*startContainer)) {
3989 if (&ancestor == editableRoot)
3990 break;
3991
3992 auto* renderer = ancestor.renderer();
3993 if (!renderer)
3994 continue;
3995
3996 if (is<HTMLUListElement>(ancestor) || is<HTMLOListElement>(ancestor))
3997 enclosingLists.append(ancestor);
3998 }
3999
4000 Vector<TextList> textLists;
4001 textLists.reserveCapacity(enclosingLists.size());
4002 for (auto iterator = enclosingLists.rbegin(); iterator != enclosingLists.rend(); ++iterator) {
4003 auto& list = iterator->get();
4004 bool ordered = is<HTMLOListElement>(list);
4005 textLists.uncheckedAppend({ list.renderer()->style().listStyleType(), ordered ? downcast<HTMLOListElement>(list).start() : 1, ordered });
4006 }
4007
4008 return textLists;
4009}

4011FontAttributes Editor::fontAttributesAtSelectionStart()
4012{
4013 RefPtr<Node> nodeToRemove;
4014 auto nodeRemovalScope = WTF::makeScopeExit([&nodeToRemove]() {
4015 if (nodeToRemove)
4016 nodeToRemove->remove();
4017 });
4018
4019 auto* style = styleForSelectionStart(nodeToRemove);
4020 if (!style)
4021 return { };
4022
4023 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
4024
4025 FontAttributes attributes;
4026 platformFontAttributesAtSelectionStart(attributes, *style);
4027
4028 // FIXME: for now, always report the colors after applying -apple-color-filter. In future not all clients
4029 // may want this, so we may have to add a setting to control it. See also editingAttributedStringFromRange().
4030 auto backgroundColor = style->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
4031 if (backgroundColor.isVisible())
4032 attributes.backgroundColor = backgroundColor;
4033
4034 auto foregroundColor = style->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyColor);
4035 // FIXME: isBlackColor not suitable for dark mode.
4036 if (foregroundColor.isValid() && !Color::isBlackColor(foregroundColor))
4037 attributes.foregroundColor = foregroundColor;
4038
4039 if (auto* shadowData = style->textShadow())
4040 attributes.fontShadow = { shadowData->color(), { static_cast<float>(shadowData->x()), static_cast<float>(shadowData->y()) }, static_cast<double>(shadowData->radius()) };
4041
4042 switch (style->verticalAlign()) {
4043 case VerticalAlign::Baseline:
4044 case VerticalAlign::Bottom:
4045 case VerticalAlign::BaselineMiddle:
4046 case VerticalAlign::Length:
4047 case VerticalAlign::Middle:
4048 case VerticalAlign::TextBottom:
4049 case VerticalAlign::TextTop:
4050 case VerticalAlign::Top:
4051 break;
4052 case VerticalAlign::Sub:
4053 attributes.subscriptOrSuperscript = FontAttributes::SubscriptOrSuperscript::Subscript;
4054 break;
4055 case VerticalAlign::Super:
4056 attributes.subscriptOrSuperscript = FontAttributes::SubscriptOrSuperscript::Superscript;
4057 break;
4058 }
4059
4060 attributes.textLists = editableTextListsAtPositionInDescendingOrder(m_document.selection().selection().start());
4061
4062 switch (style->textAlign()) {
4063 case TextAlignMode::Right:
4064 case TextAlignMode::WebKitRight:
4065 attributes.horizontalAlignment = FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Right;
4066 break;
4067 case TextAlignMode::Left:
4068 case TextAlignMode::WebKitLeft:
4069 attributes.horizontalAlignment = FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Left;
4070 break;
4071 case TextAlignMode::Center:
4072 case TextAlignMode::WebKitCenter:
4073 attributes.horizontalAlignment = FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Center;
4074 break;
4075 case TextAlignMode::Justify:
4076 attributes.horizontalAlignment = FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Justify;
4077 break;
4078 case TextAlignMode::Start:
4079 if (style->hasExplicitlySetDirection())
4080 attributes.horizontalAlignment = style->isLeftToRightDirection() ? FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Left : FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Right;
4081 else
4082 attributes.horizontalAlignment = FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Natural;
4083 break;
4084 case TextAlignMode::End:
4085 attributes.horizontalAlignment = style->isLeftToRightDirection() ? FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Right : FontAttributes::HorizontalAlignment::Left;
4086 break;
4087 }
4088
4089 auto typingStyle = makeRefPtr(m_document.selection().typingStyle());
4090 if (typingStyle && typingStyle->style()) {
4091 auto value = typingStyle->style()->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
4092 if (value && value->isValueList()) {
4093 CSSValueList& valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(*value);
4094 if (valueList.hasValue(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough).ptr()))
4095 attributes.hasStrikeThrough = true;
4096 if (valueList.hasValue(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline).ptr()))
4097 attributes.hasUnderline = true;
4098 }
4099 } else {
4100 auto decoration = style->textDecorationsInEffect();
4101 if (decoration & TextDecoration::LineThrough)
4102 attributes.hasStrikeThrough = true;
4103 if (decoration & TextDecoration::Underline)
4104 attributes.hasUnderline = true;
4105 }
4106
4107 return attributes;
4108}

4224 m_isHandlingAcceptedCandidate = true;

4272// FIXME: This figures out the current style by inserting a <span>!
4273const RenderStyle* Editor::styleForSelectionStart(RefPtr<Node>& nodeToRemove)
4274{
4275 nodeToRemove = nullptr;
4276
4277 if (document().selection().isNone())
4278 return nullptr;
4279
4280 Position position = adjustedSelectionStartForStyleComputation(document().selection().selection());
4281 if (!position.isCandidate() || position.isNull())
4282 return nullptr;
4283
4284 auto typingStyle = makeRefPtr(document().selection().typingStyle());
4285 if (!typingStyle || !typingStyle->style())
4286 return &position.deprecatedNode()->renderer()->style();
4287
4288 auto styleElement = HTMLSpanElement::create(document());
4289
4290 String styleText = typingStyle->style()->asText() + " display: inline";
4291 styleElement->setAttribute(HTMLNames::styleAttr, styleText);
4292
4293 styleElement->appendChild(document().createEditingTextNode(emptyString()));
4294
4295 auto positionNode = position.deprecatedNode();
4296 ASSERT(positionNode);
4297 auto parent = makeRefPtr(positionNode->parentNode());
4298 if (!parent || parent->appendChild(styleElement.get()).hasException())
4299 return nullptr;
4300
4301 nodeToRemove = styleElement.ptr();
4302
4303 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
4304 return styleElement->renderer() ? &styleElement->renderer()->style() : nullptr;

4307RefPtr<Font> Editor::fontForSelection(bool& hasMultipleFonts)
4308{
4309 hasMultipleFonts = false;
4310
4311 if (!m_document.selection().isRange()) {
4312 RefPtr<Node> nodeToRemove;
4313 RefPtr<Font> font;
4314 {
4315 auto* style = styleForSelectionStart(nodeToRemove);
4316 if (!style)
4317 return nullptr;
4318 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
4319 font = const_cast<Font*>(&style->fontCascade().primaryFont());
4320 }
4321
4322 if (nodeToRemove)
4323 nodeToRemove->remove();
4324
4325 return font;
4326 }
4327
4328 auto range = m_document.selection().selection().toNormalizedRange();
4329 if (!range)
4330 return nullptr;
4331
4332 // FIXME: Adjusting the start may move it past the end. In that case the iterator below will go on to the end of the document.
4333 auto adjustedStart = makeBoundaryPoint(adjustedSelectionStartForStyleComputation(m_document.selection().selection()));
4334 if (!adjustedStart)
4335 return nullptr;
4336 range->start = *adjustedStart;
4337
4338 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
4339
4340 RefPtr<Font> font;
4341 for (auto& node : intersectingNodes(*range)) {
4342 auto renderer = node.renderer();
4343 if (!renderer)
4344 continue;
4345 auto& primaryFont = renderer->style().fontCascade().primaryFont();
4346 if (!font)
4347 font = const_cast<Font*>(&primaryFont);
4348 else if (font != &primaryFont) {
4349 hasMultipleFonts = true;
4350 break;
4351 }
4352 }
4353
4354 return font;
4355}
